52 Operand StackArgumentsAccessor::GetArgumentOperand(int index) const {
53  DCHECK_GE(index, 0);
54  // arg[0] = rsp + kPCOnStackSize;
55  // arg[i] = arg[0] + i * kSystemPointerSize;
56  return Operand(rsp, kPCOnStackSize + index * kSystemPointerSize);
57 }
58 
59 void MacroAssembler::CodeEntry() {
60  endbr64();
61 }
62 
63 void MacroAssembler::Load(Register destination, ExternalReference source) {
64  if (root_array_available_ && options().enable_root_relative_access) {
65  intptr_t delta = RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), source);
66  if (is_int32(delta)) {
67  movq(destination, Operand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(delta)));
68  return;
69  }
70  }
71  // Safe code.
72  if (destination == rax && !options().isolate_independent_code) {
73  load_rax(source);
74  } else {
75  movq(destination, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(source));
76  }
77 }
78 
79 void MacroAssembler::Store(ExternalReference destination, Register source) {
80  if (root_array_available_ && options().enable_root_relative_access) {
81  intptr_t delta =
82  RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), destination);
83  if (is_int32(delta)) {
84  movq(Operand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(delta)), source);
85  return;
86  }
87  }
88  // Safe code.
89  if (source == rax && !options().isolate_independent_code) {
90  store_rax(destination);
91  } else {
92  movq(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(destination), source);
93  }
94 }
95 
96 void MacroAssembler::LoadFromConstantsTable(Register destination,
97  int constant_index) {
98  DCHECK(RootsTable::IsImmortalImmovable(RootIndex::kBuiltinsConstantsTable));
99  LoadRoot(destination, RootIndex::kBuiltinsConstantsTable);
100  LoadTaggedField(
101  destination,
102  FieldOperand(destination, FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(constant_index)));
103 }

105 void MacroAssembler::LoadRootRegisterOffset(Register destination,
106  intptr_t offset) {
107  DCHECK(is_int32(offset));
108  if (offset == 0) {
109  Move(destination, kRootRegister);
110  } else {
111  leaq(destination, Operand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset)));
112  }
113 }
114 
115 void MacroAssembler::LoadRootRelative(Register destination, int32_t offset) {
116  movq(destination, Operand(kRootRegister, offset));
117 }
118 
119 void MacroAssembler::StoreRootRelative(int32_t offset, Register value) {
120  movq(Operand(kRootRegister, offset), value);
121 }
122 
123 void MacroAssembler::LoadAddress(Register destination,
124  ExternalReference source) {
125  if (root_array_available()) {
126  if (source.IsIsolateFieldId()) {
127  leaq(destination,
128  Operand(kRootRegister, source.offset_from_root_register()));
129  return;
130  }
131  if (options().enable_root_relative_access) {
132  intptr_t delta =
133  RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), source);
134  if (is_int32(delta)) {
135  leaq(destination, Operand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(delta)));
136  return;
137  }
138  } else if (options().isolate_independent_code) {
139  IndirectLoadExternalReference(destination, source);
140  return;
141  }
142  }
143  Move(destination, source);
144 }
145 
146 Operand MacroAssembler::ExternalReferenceAsOperand(ExternalReference reference,
147  Register scratch) {
148  if (root_array_available()) {
149  if (reference.IsIsolateFieldId()) {
150  return Operand(kRootRegister, reference.offset_from_root_register());
151  }
152  if (options().enable_root_relative_access) {
153  int64_t delta =
154  RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
155  if (is_int32(delta)) {
156  return Operand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(delta));
157  }
158  }
159  if (options().isolate_independent_code) {
160  if (IsAddressableThroughRootRegister(isolate(), reference)) {
161  // Some external references can be efficiently loaded as an offset from
162  // kRootRegister.
163  intptr_t offset =
164  RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
165  CHECK(is_int32(offset));
166  return Operand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
167  } else {
168  // Otherwise, do a memory load from the external reference table.
169  movq(scratch, Operand(kRootRegister,
170  RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReferenceTableEntry(
171  isolate(), reference)));
172  return Operand(scratch, 0);
173  }
174  }
175  }
176  Move(scratch, reference);
177  return Operand(scratch, 0);
178 }
179 
180 void MacroAssembler::PushAddress(ExternalReference source) {
181  LoadAddress(kScratchRegister, source);
182  Push(kScratchRegister);
183 }
184 
185 Operand MacroAssembler::RootAsOperand(RootIndex index) {
186  DCHECK(root_array_available());
187  return Operand(kRootRegister, RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(index));
188 }
189 
190 void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedRoot(Register destination, RootIndex index) {
191  static_assert(!CanBeImmediate(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue) ||
192  std::is_same_v<Tagged_t, uint32_t>);
193  if (CanBeImmediate(index)) {
194  mov_tagged(destination,
195  Immediate(static_cast<uint32_t>(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))));
196  return;
197  }
198  DCHECK(root_array_available_);
199  movq(destination, RootAsOperand(index));
200 }
201 
202 void MacroAssembler::LoadRoot(Register destination, RootIndex index) {
203  if (CanBeImmediate(index)) {
204  DecompressTagged(destination,
205  static_cast<uint32_t>(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index)));
206  return;
207  }
208  DCHECK(root_array_available_);
209  movq(destination, RootAsOperand(index));
210 }
211 
212 void MacroAssembler::PushRoot(RootIndex index) {
213  DCHECK(root_array_available_);
214  Push(RootAsOperand(index));
215 }
216 
217 void MacroAssembler::CompareRoot(Register with, RootIndex index,
218  ComparisonMode mode) {
219  if (mode == ComparisonMode::kFullPointer ||
220  !base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
221  RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot)) {
222  // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
223  cmpq(with, RootAsOperand(index));
224  return;
225  }
226  CompareTaggedRoot(with, index);
227 }
228 
229 void MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedRoot(Register with, RootIndex index) {
230  AssertSmiOrHeapObjectInMainCompressionCage(with);
231  if (CanBeImmediate(index)) {
232  cmp_tagged(with, Immediate(static_cast<uint32_t>(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))));
233  return;
234  }
235  DCHECK(root_array_available_);
236  // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
237  DCHECK(base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
238  RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot));
239  cmp_tagged(with, RootAsOperand(index));
240 }
241 
242 void MacroAssembler::CompareRoot(Operand with, RootIndex index) {
243  if (CanBeImmediate(index)) {
244  cmp_tagged(with, Immediate(static_cast<uint32_t>(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))));
245  return;
246  }
247  DCHECK(root_array_available_);
248  DCHECK(!with.AddressUsesRegister(kScratchRegister));
249  if (base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
250  RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot)) {
251  mov_tagged(kScratchRegister, RootAsOperand(index));
252  cmp_tagged(with, kScratchRegister);
253  } else {
254  // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
255  movq(kScratchRegister, RootAsOperand(index));
256  cmpq(with, kScratchRegister);
257  }
258 }

260 void MacroAssembler::LoadCompressedMap(Register destination, Register object) {
261  CHECK(COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL);
262  mov_tagged(destination, FieldOperand(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
263 }

265 void MacroAssembler::LoadMap(Register destination, Register object) {
266  LoadTaggedField(destination, FieldOperand(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
267 #ifdef V8_MAP_PACKING
268  UnpackMapWord(destination);
269 #endif
270 }
271 
272 void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVector(Register dst, Register closure,
273  Label* fbv_undef,
274  Label::Distance distance) {
275  Label done;
276 
277  // Load the feedback vector from the closure.
278  TaggedRegister feedback_cell(dst);
279  LoadTaggedField(feedback_cell,
280  FieldOperand(closure, JSFunction::kFeedbackCellOffset));
281  LoadTaggedField(dst, FieldOperand(feedback_cell, FeedbackCell::kValueOffset));
282 
283  // Check if feedback vector is valid.
284  IsObjectType(dst, FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE, rcx);
285  j(equal, &done, Label::kNear);
286 
287  // Not valid, load undefined.
288  LoadRoot(dst, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
289  jmp(fbv_undef, distance);
290 
291  bind(&done);
292 }

294 void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedField(Register destination,
295  Operand field_operand) {
296  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
297  DecompressTagged(destination, field_operand);
298  } else {
299  mov_tagged(destination, field_operand);
300  }
301 }

303 void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedField(TaggedRegister destination,
304  Operand field_operand) {
305  LoadTaggedFieldWithoutDecompressing(destination.reg(), field_operand);
306 }

308 void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedFieldWithoutDecompressing(
309  Register destination, Operand field_operand) {
310  mov_tagged(destination, field_operand);
311 }

313 #ifdef V8_MAP_PACKING
314 void MacroAssembler::UnpackMapWord(Register r) {
315  // Clear the top two bytes (which may include metadata). Must be in sync with
316  // MapWord::Unpack, and vice versa.
317  shlq(r, Immediate(16));
318  shrq(r, Immediate(16));
319  xorq(r, Immediate(Internals::kMapWordXorMask));
320 }
321 #endif

323 void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedSignedField(Register destination,
324  Operand field_operand) {
325  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
326  DecompressTaggedSigned(destination, field_operand);
327  } else {
328  mov_tagged(destination, field_operand);
329  }
330 }

332 void MacroAssembler::PushTaggedField(Operand field_operand, Register scratch) {
333  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
334  DCHECK(!field_operand.AddressUsesRegister(scratch));
335  DecompressTagged(scratch, field_operand);
336  Push(scratch);
337  } else {
338  Push(field_operand);
339  }
340 }

368 void MacroAssembler::StoreTaggedSignedField(Operand dst_field_operand,
369  Tagged<Smi> value) {
370  if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
371  Move(kScratchRegister, value);
372  movq(dst_field_operand, kScratchRegister);
373  } else {
374  StoreTaggedField(dst_field_operand, Immediate(value));
375  }

378 void MacroAssembler::AtomicStoreTaggedField(Operand dst_field_operand,
379  Register value) {
380  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
381  movl(kScratchRegister, value);
382  xchgl(kScratchRegister, dst_field_operand);
383  } else {
384  movq(kScratchRegister, value);
385  xchgq(kScratchRegister, dst_field_operand);
386  }
387 }

409  Tagged_t immediate) {

415 void MacroAssembler::DecompressProtected(Register destination,
416  Operand field_operand) {
417 #if V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
418  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
419  movl(destination, field_operand);
420  DCHECK(root_array_available_);
421  orq(destination,
422  Operand{kRootRegister, IsolateData::trusted_cage_base_offset()});
423 #else
424  UNREACHABLE();
425 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
426 }

428 void MacroAssembler::RecordWriteField(Register object, int offset,
429  Register value, Register slot_address,
430  SaveFPRegsMode save_fp,
431  SmiCheck smi_check,
432  ReadOnlyCheck ro_check,
433  SlotDescriptor slot) {
434  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
435  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value, slot_address));
436  // First, check if a write barrier is even needed. The tests below
437  // catch stores of Smis and read-only objects.
438  Label done;
439 
440 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
441  if (ro_check == ReadOnlyCheck::kInline) {
442  // Quick check for Read-only and small Smi values.
443  static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kLastAllocatedRoot < kRegularPageSize);
444  JumpIfUnsignedLessThan(value, kRegularPageSize, &done);
445  }
446 #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
447 
448  // Skip barrier if writing a smi.
449  if (smi_check == SmiCheck::kInline) {
450  JumpIfSmi(value, &done);
451  }
452 
453  // Although the object register is tagged, the offset is relative to the start
454  // of the object, so the offset must be a multiple of kTaggedSize.
455  DCHECK(IsAligned(offset, kTaggedSize));
456 
457  leaq(slot_address, FieldOperand(object, offset));
458  if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
459  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, "Debug check slot_address");
460  Label ok;
461  testb(slot_address, Immediate(kTaggedSize - 1));
462  j(zero, &ok, Label::kNear);
463  int3();
464  bind(&ok);
465  }
466 
467  RecordWrite(object, slot_address, value, save_fp, SmiCheck::kOmit,
468  ReadOnlyCheck::kOmit, slot);
469 
470  bind(&done);
471 
472  // Clobber clobbered input registers when running with the debug-code flag
473  // turned on to provoke errors.
474  if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
475  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, "Zap scratch registers");
476  Move(value, kZapValue, RelocInfo::NO_INFO);
477  Move(slot_address, kZapValue, RelocInfo::NO_INFO);
478  }
479 }
480 
481 void MacroAssembler::EnterSandbox() {
482 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_HARDWARE_SUPPORT
483  pushq(rax);
484  pushq(rbx);
485  pushq(rcx);
486  pushq(rdx);
487 
488  xorq(rcx, rcx);
489  xorq(rdx, rdx);
490 
491  // TODO(350324877): it would be nicer if we could use an IsolateFieldId here.
492  // However, that isn't currently possible since these routines are also used
493  // in code that doesn't have the root register available. In the future, we
494  // might anyway want to refactor this mechanism to instead use dedicated
495  // trampoline builtins for entering/exiting sandboxed execution mode. Then we
496  // could consider generating the code for that trampoline at runtime, at
497  // which point we would no longer need an external reference at all.
498  LoadAddress(rbx, ExternalReference::sandboxed_mode_pkey_mask_address());
499  movl(rbx, Operand(rbx, 0));
500 
501  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
502  // Check that we are not in sandboxed mode.
503  // If sandbox hardware support is not active, the mask will be all zeroes
504  // and so this test will also pass.
505  rdpkru();
506  andl(rax, rbx);
507  Assert(zero, AbortReason::kUnexpectedSandboxMode);
508  }
509 
510  // PKEY permissions bits:
511  // 00: kNoRestrictions
512  // 01: kDisableAccess
513  // 10: kDisableWrite
514  rdpkru();
515  // Set the bit from the pkey mask, thereby restricting access to the
516  // out-of-sandbox pkey.
517  orl(rax, rbx);
518  wrpkru();
519 
520  popq(rdx);
521  popq(rcx);
522  popq(rbx);
523  popq(rax);
524 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_HARDWARE_SUPPORT
525 }
526 
527 void MacroAssembler::ExitSandbox() {
528 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_HARDWARE_SUPPORT
529  pushq(rax);
530  pushq(rbx);
531  pushq(rcx);
532  pushq(rdx);
533 
534  xorq(rcx, rcx);
535  xorq(rdx, rdx);
536 
537  LoadAddress(rbx, ExternalReference::sandboxed_mode_pkey_mask_address());
538  movl(rbx, Operand(rbx, 0));
539 
540  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
541  // Check that we are in sandboxed mode.
542  // If sandbox hardware support is not active, the mask will be all zeroes
543  // and so we need to handle this here.
544  Label hardware_support_not_active;
545  testl(rbx, rbx);
546  j(zero, &hardware_support_not_active);
547  rdpkru();
548  andl(rax, rbx);
549  Assert(not_zero, AbortReason::kUnexpectedSandboxMode);
550  bind(&hardware_support_not_active);
551  }
552 
553  // PKEY permissions bits:
554  // 00: kNoRestrictions
555  // 01: kDisableAccess
556  // 10: kDisableWrite
557  rdpkru();
558  // Clear the bit from the pkey mask, thereby restoring full access to the
559  // out-of-sandbox pkey.
560  notl(rbx);
561  andl(rax, rbx);
562  wrpkru();
563 
564  popq(rdx);
565  popq(rcx);
566  popq(rbx);
567  popq(rax);
568 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_HARDWARE_SUPPORT
569 }
570 
571 void MacroAssembler::AssertInSandboxedExecutionMode() {
572 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_HARDWARE_SUPPORT
573  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
574  pushq(rax);
575  pushq(rbx);
576  pushq(rcx);
577  pushq(rdx);
578 
579  xorq(rcx, rcx);
580  xorq(rdx, rdx);
581 
582  LoadAddress(rbx, ExternalReference::sandboxed_mode_pkey_mask_address());
583  movl(rbx, Operand(rbx, 0));
584 
585  // If sandbox hardware support is not active, the mask will be all zeroes
586  // and so we need to handle this here.
587  Label hardware_support_not_active;
588  testl(rbx, rbx);
589  j(zero, &hardware_support_not_active);
590 
591  rdpkru();
592  andl(rax, rbx);
593  Assert(not_zero, AbortReason::kUnexpectedSandboxMode);
594 
595  bind(&hardware_support_not_active);
596 
597  popq(rdx);
598  popq(rcx);
599  popq(rbx);
600  popq(rax);
601  }
602 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_HARDWARE_SUPPORT
603 }
604 
605 void MacroAssembler::SwitchSandboxingModeTo(CodeSandboxingMode mode) {
606  switch (mode) {
607  case CodeSandboxingMode::kSandboxed:
608  return EnterSandbox();
609  case CodeSandboxingMode::kUnsandboxed:
610  return ExitSandbox();
611  }
612 }
613 
614 void MacroAssembler::SwitchSandboxingModeBeforeCallIfNeeded(
615  CodeSandboxingMode target_sandboxing_mode) {
616  if (sandboxing_mode() != target_sandboxing_mode) {
617  SwitchSandboxingModeTo(target_sandboxing_mode);
618  }
619 }
620 
621 void MacroAssembler::SwitchSandboxingModeAfterCallIfNeeded(
622  CodeSandboxingMode target_sandboxing_mode) {
623  if (sandboxing_mode() != target_sandboxing_mode) {
624  SwitchSandboxingModeTo(sandboxing_mode());
625  }
626 }
627 
628 void MacroAssembler::EncodeSandboxedPointer(Register value) {
629  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
630 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
631  subq(value, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister);
632  shlq(value, Immediate(kSandboxedPointerShift));
633 #else
634  UNREACHABLE();
635 #endif
636 }
637 
638 void MacroAssembler::DecodeSandboxedPointer(Register value) {
639  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
640 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
641  shrq(value, Immediate(kSandboxedPointerShift));
642  addq(value, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister);
643 #else
644  UNREACHABLE();
645 #endif
646 }
647 
648 void MacroAssembler::LoadSandboxedPointerField(Register destination,
649  Operand field_operand) {
650  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
651  movq(destination, field_operand);
652  DecodeSandboxedPointer(destination);
653 }
654 
655 void MacroAssembler::StoreSandboxedPointerField(Operand dst_field_operand,
656  Register value) {
657  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
658  DCHECK(!AreAliased(value, kScratchRegister));
659  DCHECK(!dst_field_operand.AddressUsesRegister(kScratchRegister));
660  movq(kScratchRegister, value);
661  EncodeSandboxedPointer(kScratchRegister);
662  movq(dst_field_operand, kScratchRegister);
663 }
664 
665 void MacroAssembler::LoadExternalPointerField(
666  Register destination, Operand field_operand,
667  ExternalPointerTagRange tag_range, Register scratch,
668  IsolateRootLocation isolateRootLocation) {
669  DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, scratch));
670 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
671  DCHECK(!tag_range.IsEmpty());
672  DCHECK(!IsSharedExternalPointerType(tag_range));
673  DCHECK(!field_operand.AddressUsesRegister(scratch));
674  if (isolateRootLocation == IsolateRootLocation::kInRootRegister) {
675  DCHECK(root_array_available_);
676  // TODO(saelo): consider using an ExternalReference here.
677  movq(scratch,
678  Operand(kRootRegister,
679  IsolateData::external_pointer_table_offset() +
680  Internals::kExternalPointerTableBasePointerOffset));
681  } else {
682  DCHECK(isolateRootLocation == IsolateRootLocation::kInScratchRegister);
683  movq(scratch,
684  Operand(scratch,
685  IsolateData::external_pointer_table_offset() +
686  Internals::kExternalPointerTableBasePointerOffset));
687  }
688  movl(destination, field_operand);
689  shrq(destination, Immediate(kExternalPointerIndexShift));
690  static_assert(kExternalPointerTableEntrySize == 8);
691  movq(destination, Operand(scratch, destination, times_8, 0));
692 
693  // We don't expect to see empty fields here. If this is ever needed, consider
694  // using an dedicated empty value entry for those tags instead (i.e. an entry
695  // with the right tag and nullptr payload).
696  DCHECK(!ExternalPointerCanBeEmpty(tag_range));
697 
698  if (tag_range.Size() == 1) {
699  // The common and simple case: we expect exactly one tag.
700  movq(scratch, destination);
701  shrq(scratch, Immediate(kExternalPointerTagShift));
702  andl(scratch, Immediate(kExternalPointerShiftedTagMask));
703  cmpl(scratch, Immediate(tag_range.first));
704  SbxCheck(equal, AbortReason::kExternalPointerTagMismatch);
705  movq(scratch, Immediate64(kExternalPointerPayloadMask));
706  andq(destination, scratch);
707  } else {
708  // Not currently supported. Implement once needed.
709  DCHECK_NE(tag_range, kAnyExternalPointerTagRange);
710  UNREACHABLE();
711  }
712 #else
713  movq(destination, field_operand);
714 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
715 }
716 
717 void MacroAssembler::LoadTrustedPointerField(Register destination,
718  Operand field_operand,
719  IndirectPointerTag tag,
720  Register scratch) {
721 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
722  LoadIndirectPointerField(destination, field_operand, tag, scratch);
723 #else
724  LoadTaggedField(destination, field_operand);
725 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
726 }
727 
728 void MacroAssembler::StoreTrustedPointerField(Operand dst_field_operand,
729  Register value) {
730 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
731  StoreIndirectPointerField(dst_field_operand, value);
732 #else
733  StoreTaggedField(dst_field_operand, value);
734 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
735 }
736 
737 void MacroAssembler::LoadIndirectPointerField(Register destination,
738  Operand field_operand,
739  IndirectPointerTag tag,
740  Register scratch) {
741 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
742  DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, scratch));
743  Register handle = scratch;
744  movl(handle, field_operand);
745  ResolveIndirectPointerHandle(destination, handle, tag);
746 #else
747  UNREACHABLE();
748 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
749 }
750 
751 void MacroAssembler::StoreIndirectPointerField(Operand dst_field_operand,
752  Register value) {
753 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
754  movl(kScratchRegister,
755  FieldOperand(value, ExposedTrustedObject::kSelfIndirectPointerOffset));
756  movl(dst_field_operand, kScratchRegister);
757 #else
758  UNREACHABLE();
759 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
760 }
761 
762 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
763 void MacroAssembler::ResolveIndirectPointerHandle(Register destination,
764  Register handle,
765  IndirectPointerTag tag) {
766  // The tag implies which pointer table to use.
767  if (tag == kUnknownIndirectPointerTag) {
768  // In this case we have to rely on the handle marking to determine which
769  // pointer table to use.
770  Label is_trusted_pointer_handle, done;
771  testl(handle, Immediate(kCodePointerHandleMarker));
772  j(zero, &is_trusted_pointer_handle, Label::kNear);
773  ResolveCodePointerHandle(destination, handle);
774  jmp(&done, Label::kNear);
775  bind(&is_trusted_pointer_handle);
776  ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(destination, handle,
777  kUnknownIndirectPointerTag);
778  bind(&done);
779  } else if (tag == kCodeIndirectPointerTag) {
780  ResolveCodePointerHandle(destination, handle);
781  } else {
782  ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(destination, handle, tag);
783  }
784 }
785 
786 void MacroAssembler::ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(Register destination,
787  Register handle,
788  IndirectPointerTag tag) {
789  DCHECK_NE(tag, kCodeIndirectPointerTag);
790  DCHECK(!AreAliased(handle, destination));
791  shrl(handle, Immediate(kTrustedPointerHandleShift));
792  static_assert(kTrustedPointerTableEntrySize == 8);
793  DCHECK(root_array_available_);
794  movq(destination,
795  Operand{kRootRegister, IsolateData::trusted_pointer_table_offset()});
796  movq(destination, Operand{destination, handle, times_8, 0});
797  // Untag the pointer and remove the marking bit in one operation.
798  Register tag_reg = handle;
799  movq(tag_reg, Immediate64(~(tag | kTrustedPointerTableMarkBit)));
800  andq(destination, tag_reg);
801 }
802 
803 void MacroAssembler::ResolveCodePointerHandle(Register destination,
804  Register handle) {
805  DCHECK(!AreAliased(handle, destination));
806  Register table = destination;
807  LoadCodePointerTableBase(table);
808  shrl(handle, Immediate(kCodePointerHandleShift));
809  // The code pointer table entry size is 16 bytes, so we have to do an
810  // explicit shift first (times_16 doesn't exist).
811  shll(handle, Immediate(kCodePointerTableEntrySizeLog2));
812  movq(destination,
813  Operand(table, handle, times_1, kCodePointerTableEntryCodeObjectOffset));
814  // The LSB is used as marking bit by the code pointer table, so here we have
815  // to set it using a bitwise OR as it may or may not be set.
816  orq(destination, Immediate(kHeapObjectTag));
817 }
818 
819 void MacroAssembler::LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(Register destination,
820  Operand field_operand,
821  CodeEntrypointTag tag) {
822  DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, kScratchRegister));
823  DCHECK(!field_operand.AddressUsesRegister(kScratchRegister));
824  DCHECK_NE(tag, kInvalidEntrypointTag);
825  LoadCodePointerTableBase(kScratchRegister);
826  movl(destination, field_operand);
827  shrl(destination, Immediate(kCodePointerHandleShift));
828  shll(destination, Immediate(kCodePointerTableEntrySizeLog2));
829  movq(destination, Operand(kScratchRegister, destination, times_1, 0));
830  if (tag != 0) {
831  // Can this be improved?
832  movq(kScratchRegister, Immediate64(tag));
833  xorq(destination, kScratchRegister);
834  }
835 }
836 
837 void MacroAssembler::LoadCodePointerTableBase(Register destination) {
838 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS_IN_MULTIPLE_CAGES
839  if (!options().isolate_independent_code && isolate()) {
840  // Embed the code pointer table address into the code.
841  LoadAddress(destination,
842  ExternalReference::code_pointer_table_base_address(isolate()));
843  } else {
844  // Force indirect load via root register as a workaround for
845  // isolate-independent code (for example, for Wasm).
846  Load(destination,
847  ExternalReference::address_of_code_pointer_table_base_address());
848  }
849 #else
850  // Embed the code pointer table address into the code.
851  LoadAddress(destination,
852  ExternalReference::global_code_pointer_table_base_address());
853 #endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS_IN_MULTIPLE_CAGES
854 }
855 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
856 
857 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
858 void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(
859  Register destination, Register dispatch_handle) {
860  DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, dispatch_handle, kScratchRegister));
861  CHECK(root_array_available());
862  movq(kScratchRegister,
863  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kJSDispatchTable));
864  movq(destination, dispatch_handle);
865  shrl(destination, Immediate(kJSDispatchHandleShift));
866  shll(destination, Immediate(kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2));
867  movq(destination, Operand(kScratchRegister, destination, times_1,
868  JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset));
869 }
870 
871 void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(
872  Register destination, JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle) {
873  DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, kScratchRegister));
874  CHECK(root_array_available());
875  movq(kScratchRegister,
876  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kJSDispatchTable));
877  // WARNING: This offset calculation is only safe if we have already stored a
878  // RelocInfo for the dispatch handle, e.g. in CallJSDispatchEntry, (thus
879  // keeping the dispatch entry alive) _and_ because the entrypoints are not
880  // compatible (thus meaning that the offset calculation is not invalidated by
881  // a compaction).
882  // TODO(leszeks): Make this less of a footgun.
883  static_assert(!JSDispatchTable::kSupportsCompaction);
884  int offset = JSDispatchTable::OffsetOfEntry(dispatch_handle) +
885  JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset;
886  movq(destination, Operand(kScratchRegister, offset));
887 }
888 
889 void MacroAssembler::LoadParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(
890  Register destination, Register dispatch_handle) {
891  DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, dispatch_handle, kScratchRegister));
892  CHECK(root_array_available());
893  movq(kScratchRegister,
894  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kJSDispatchTable));
895  movq(destination, dispatch_handle);
896  shrl(destination, Immediate(kJSDispatchHandleShift));
897  shll(destination, Immediate(kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2));
898  static_assert(JSDispatchEntry::kParameterCountMask == 0xffff);
899  movzxwq(destination, Operand(kScratchRegister, destination, times_1,
900  JSDispatchEntry::kCodeObjectOffset));
901 }
902 
903 void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointAndParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(
904  Register entrypoint, Register parameter_count, Register dispatch_handle) {
905  DCHECK(!AreAliased(entrypoint, parameter_count, dispatch_handle,
906  kScratchRegister));
907  CHECK(root_array_available());
908  movq(kScratchRegister,
909  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kJSDispatchTable));
910  Register offset = parameter_count;
911  movq(offset, dispatch_handle);
912  shrl(offset, Immediate(kJSDispatchHandleShift));
913  shll(offset, Immediate(kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2));
914  movq(entrypoint, Operand(kScratchRegister, offset, times_1,
915  JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset));
916  static_assert(JSDispatchEntry::kParameterCountMask == 0xffff);
917  movzxwq(parameter_count, Operand(kScratchRegister, offset, times_1,
918  JSDispatchEntry::kCodeObjectOffset));
919 }
920 #endif

922 void MacroAssembler::LoadProtectedPointerField(Register destination,
923  Operand field_operand) {

932 void MacroAssembler::CallEphemeronKeyBarrier(Register object,
933  Register slot_address,
934  SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode) {
935  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
936  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, slot_address));
937  RegList registers =
938  WriteBarrierDescriptor::ComputeSavedRegisters(object, slot_address);
939  PushAll(registers);
940 
941  Register object_parameter = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
942  Register slot_address_parameter =
943  WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister();
944  MovePair(slot_address_parameter, slot_address, object_parameter, object);
945 
946  CallBuiltin(Builtins::EphemeronKeyBarrier(fp_mode));
947  PopAll(registers);
948 }

950 void MacroAssembler::CallIndirectPointerBarrier(Register object,
951  Register slot_address,
952  SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
953  IndirectPointerTag tag) {
954  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
955  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, slot_address));
956  // TODO(saelo) if necessary, we could introduce a "SaveRegisters version of
957  // this function and make this code not save clobbered registers. It's
958  // probably not currently worth the effort though since stores to indirect
959  // pointer fields are fairly rare.
960  RegList registers =
961  IndirectPointerWriteBarrierDescriptor::ComputeSavedRegisters(
962  object, slot_address);
963  PushAll(registers);
964 
965  Register object_parameter =
966  IndirectPointerWriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
967  Register slot_address_parameter =
968  IndirectPointerWriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister();
969  MovePair(slot_address_parameter, slot_address, object_parameter, object);
970 
971  Register tag_parameter =
972  IndirectPointerWriteBarrierDescriptor::IndirectPointerTagRegister();
973  Move(tag_parameter, tag);
974 
975  CallBuiltin(Builtins::IndirectPointerBarrier(fp_mode));
976  PopAll(registers);
977 }

997 void MacroAssembler::CallRecordWriteStub(Register object, Register slot_address,
998  SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
999  StubCallMode mode) {
1000  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1001  // Use CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters if the object and slot registers
1002  // need to be caller saved.
1003  DCHECK_EQ(WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister(), object);
1004  DCHECK_EQ(WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister(), slot_address);
1005 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1006  if (mode == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
1007  // Use {near_call} for direct Wasm call within a module.
1008  intptr_t wasm_target =
1009  static_cast<intptr_t>(wasm::WasmCode::GetRecordWriteBuiltin(fp_mode));
1010  near_call(wasm_target, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
1011 #else
1012  if (false) {
1013 #endif
1014  } else {
1015  CallBuiltin(Builtins::RecordWrite(fp_mode));
1016  }
1017 }

1019 #ifdef V8_IS_TSAN
1020 void MacroAssembler::CallTSANStoreStub(Register address, Register value,
1021  SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, int size,
1022  StubCallMode mode,
1023  std::memory_order order) {
1024  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1025  DCHECK(!AreAliased(address, value));
1026  TSANStoreDescriptor descriptor;
1027  RegList registers = descriptor.allocatable_registers();
1028 
1029  PushAll(registers);
1030 
1031  Register address_parameter(
1032  descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(TSANStoreDescriptor::kAddress));
1033  Register value_parameter(
1034  descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(TSANStoreDescriptor::kValue));
1035 
1036  // Prepare argument registers for calling GetTSANStoreStub.
1037  MovePair(address_parameter, address, value_parameter, value);
1038 
1039 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1040  if (mode != StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
1041  // JS functions and Wasm wrappers.
1042  CallBuiltin(CodeFactory::GetTSANStoreStub(fp_mode, size, order));
1043  } else {
1044  // Wasm functions should call builtins through their far jump table.
1045  auto wasm_target = static_cast<intptr_t>(
1046  wasm::WasmCode::GetTSANStoreBuiltin(fp_mode, size, order));
1047  near_call(wasm_target, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
1048  }
1049 #else
1050  CallBuiltin(CodeFactory::GetTSANStoreStub(fp_mode, size, order));
1051 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1052 
1053  PopAll(registers);
1054 }

1088 void MacroAssembler::RecordWrite(Register object, Register slot_address,
1089  Register value, SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
1090  SmiCheck smi_check, ReadOnlyCheck ro_check,
1091  SlotDescriptor slot) {
1092  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1093  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, slot_address, value));
1094  AssertNotSmi(object);
1095 
1096  if (v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) {
1097  return;
1098  }
1099 
1100  if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
1101  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, "Debug check slot_address");
1102  Label ok;
1103  if (slot.contains_indirect_pointer()) {
1104  Push(object); // Use object register as scratch
1105  Register scratch = object;
1106  Push(slot_address); // Use slot address register to load the value into
1107  Register value_in_slot = slot_address;
1108  LoadIndirectPointerField(value_in_slot, Operand(slot_address, 0),
1109  slot.indirect_pointer_tag(), scratch);
1110  cmp_tagged(value, value_in_slot);
1111  // These pops don't affect the flag registers, so we can do them before
1112  // the conditional jump below.
1113  Pop(slot_address);
1114  Pop(object);
1115  } else {
1116  cmp_tagged(value, Operand(slot_address, 0));
1117  }
1118  j(equal, &ok, Label::kNear);
1119  int3();
1120  bind(&ok);
1121  }
1122 
1123  // First, check if a write barrier is even needed. The tests below
1124  // catch stores of smis and read-only objects, as well as stores into the
1125  // young generation.
1126  Label done;
1127 
1128 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
1129  if (ro_check == ReadOnlyCheck::kInline) {
1130  // Quick check for Read-only and small Smi values.
1131  static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kLastAllocatedRoot < kRegularPageSize);
1132  JumpIfUnsignedLessThan(value, kRegularPageSize, &done);
1133  }
1134 #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
1135 
1136  if (smi_check == SmiCheck::kInline) {
1137  // Skip barrier if writing a smi.
1138  JumpIfSmi(value, &done);
1139  }
1140 
1141  if (slot.contains_indirect_pointer()) {
1142  // The indirect pointer write barrier is only enabled during marking.
1143  JumpIfNotMarking(&done);
1144  } else {
1145 #if V8_ENABLE_STICKY_MARK_BITS_BOOL
1146  DCHECK(!AreAliased(kScratchRegister, object, slot_address, value));
1147  Label stub_call;
1148 
1149  JumpIfMarking(&stub_call);
1150 
1151  // Save the slot_address in the xmm scratch register.
1152  movq(kScratchDoubleReg, slot_address);
1153  Register scratch0 = slot_address;
1154  CheckMarkBit(object, kScratchRegister, scratch0, carry, &done);
1155  CheckPageFlag(value, kScratchRegister, MemoryChunk::kIsInReadOnlyHeapMask,
1156  not_zero, &done, Label::kFar);
1157  CheckMarkBit(value, kScratchRegister, scratch0, carry, &done);
1158  movq(slot_address, kScratchDoubleReg);
1159  bind(&stub_call);
1160 #else // !V8_ENABLE_STICKY_MARK_BITS_BOOL
1161  CheckPageFlag(value,
1162  value, // Used as scratch.
1163  MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, zero, &done,
1164  Label::kFar);
1165 
1166  CheckPageFlag(object,
1167  value, // Used as scratch.
1168  MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask, zero, &done,
1169  Label::kFar);
1170 #endif // !V8_ENABLE_STICKY_MARK_BITS_BOOL
1171  }
1172 
1173  if (slot.contains_direct_pointer()) {
1174  CallRecordWriteStub(object, slot_address, fp_mode,
1175  StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
1176  } else {
1177  DCHECK(slot.contains_indirect_pointer());
1178  CallIndirectPointerBarrier(object, slot_address, fp_mode,
1179  slot.indirect_pointer_tag());
1180  }
1181 
1182  bind(&done);
1183 
1184  // Clobber clobbered registers when running with the debug-code flag
1185  // turned on to provoke errors.
1186  if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
1187  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, "Zap scratch registers");
1188  Move(slot_address, kZapValue, RelocInfo::NO_INFO);
1189  Move(value, kZapValue, RelocInfo::NO_INFO);
1190  }
1191 }
1192 
1193 void MacroAssembler::Check(Condition cc, AbortReason reason) {
1194  Label L;
1195  j(cc, &L, Label::kNear);
1196  Abort(reason);
1197  // Control will not return here.
1198  bind(&L);
1199 }
1200 
1201 void MacroAssembler::SbxCheck(Condition cc, AbortReason reason) {
1202  Check(cc, reason);
1203 }
1204 
1205 void MacroAssembler::CheckStackAlignment() {
1206  int frame_alignment = base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
1207  int frame_alignment_mask = frame_alignment - 1;
1208  if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
1209  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1210  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
1211  Label alignment_as_expected;
1212  testq(rsp, Immediate(frame_alignment_mask));
1213  j(zero, &alignment_as_expected, Label::kNear);
1214  // Abort if stack is not aligned.
1215  int3();
1216  bind(&alignment_as_expected);
1217  }
1218 }
1219 
1220 void MacroAssembler::AlignStackPointer() {
1221  const int kFrameAlignment = base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
1222  if (kFrameAlignment > 0) {
1223  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(kFrameAlignment));
1224  DCHECK(is_int8(kFrameAlignment));
1225  andq(rsp, Immediate(-kFrameAlignment));
1226  }
1227 }
1228 
1229 void MacroAssembler::Abort(AbortReason reason) {
1230  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1231  if (v8_flags.code_comments) {
1232  RecordComment("Abort message:", SourceLocation{});
1233  RecordComment(GetAbortReason(reason), SourceLocation{});
1234  }
1235 
1236  // Without debug code, save the code size and just trap.
1237  if (!v8_flags.debug_code || v8_flags.trap_on_abort) {
1238  int3();
1239  return;
1240  }
1241 
1242  if (should_abort_hard()) {
1243  // We don't care if we constructed a frame. Just pretend we did.
1244  FrameScope assume_frame(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
1245  Move(kCArgRegs[0], static_cast<int>(reason));
1246  PrepareCallCFunction(1);
1247  LoadAddress(rax, ExternalReference::abort_with_reason());
1248  call(rax);
1249  return;
1250  }
1251 
1252  Move(rdx, Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(reason)));
1253 
1254  {
1255  // We don't actually want to generate a pile of code for this, so just
1256  // claim there is a stack frame, without generating one.
1257  FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
1258  if (root_array_available()) {
1259  // Generate an indirect call via builtins entry table here in order to
1260  // ensure that the interpreter_entry_return_pc_offset is the same for
1261  // InterpreterEntryTrampoline and InterpreterEntryTrampolineForProfiling
1262  // when v8_flags.debug_code is enabled.
1263  Call(EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(Builtin::kAbort));
1264  } else {
1265  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort);
1266  }
1267  }
1268 
1269  // Control will not return here.
1270  int3();
1271 }
1272 
1273 void MacroAssembler::CallRuntime(const Runtime::Function* f,
1274  int num_arguments) {
1275  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1276  // If the expected number of arguments of the runtime function is
1277  // constant, we check that the actual number of arguments match the
1278  // expectation.
1279  CHECK(f->nargs < 0 || f->nargs == num_arguments);
1280 
1281  // TODO(1236192): Most runtime routines don't need the number of
1282  // arguments passed in because it is constant. At some point we
1283  // should remove this need and make the runtime routine entry code
1284  // smarter.
1285  Move(rax, num_arguments);
1286  LoadAddress(rbx, ExternalReference::Create(f));
1287 
1288  bool switch_to_central = options().is_wasm;
1289  CallBuiltin(Builtins::RuntimeCEntry(f->result_size, switch_to_central));
1290 }
1291 
1292 void MacroAssembler::TailCallRuntime(Runtime::FunctionId fid) {
1293  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
1294  // -- rsp[0] : return address
1295  // -- rsp[8] : argument num_arguments - 1
1296  // ...
1297  // -- rsp[8 * num_arguments] : argument 0 (receiver)
1298  //
1299  // For runtime functions with variable arguments:
1300  // -- rax : number of arguments
1301  // -----------------------------------
1302  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1303  const Runtime::Function* function = Runtime::FunctionForId(fid);
1304  DCHECK_EQ(1, function->result_size);
1305  if (function->nargs >= 0) {
1306  Move(rax, function->nargs);
1307  }
1308  JumpToExternalReference(ExternalReference::Create(fid));
1309 }
1310 
1311 void MacroAssembler::JumpToExternalReference(const ExternalReference& ext,
1312  bool builtin_exit_frame) {
1313  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1314  // Set the entry point and jump to the C entry runtime stub.
1315  LoadAddress(rbx, ext);
1316  TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::CEntry(1, ArgvMode::kStack, builtin_exit_frame));
1317 }

1319 namespace {
1320 
1321 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1322 // Only used when leaptiering is disabled.
1323 void TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(MacroAssembler* masm,
1324  Register optimized_code_entry, Register closure,
1325  Register scratch1, Register scratch2,
1326  JumpMode jump_mode) {
1327  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
1328  // rax : actual argument count
1329  // rdx : new target (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
1330  // rsi : current context, used for the runtime call
1331  // rdi : target function (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
1332  // -----------------------------------
1333  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
1334  DCHECK_EQ(closure, kJSFunctionRegister);
1335  DCHECK(!AreAliased(rax, rdx, closure, rsi, optimized_code_entry, scratch1,
1336  scratch2));
1337 
1338  Label heal_optimized_code_slot;
1339 
1340  // If the optimized code is cleared, go to runtime to update the optimization
1341  // marker field.
1342  __ LoadWeakValue(optimized_code_entry, &heal_optimized_code_slot);
1343 
1344  // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
1345  __ LoadCodePointerField(
1346  optimized_code_entry,
1347  FieldOperand(optimized_code_entry, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset), scratch1);
1348 
1349  // Check if the optimized code is marked for deopt. If it is, call the
1350  // runtime to clear it.
1351  __ AssertCode(optimized_code_entry);
1352  __ TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(optimized_code_entry);
1353  __ j(not_zero, &heal_optimized_code_slot);
1354 
1355  // Optimized code is good, get it into the closure and link the closure into
1356  // the optimized functions list, then tail call the optimized code.
1357  __ ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(optimized_code_entry, closure,
1358  scratch1, scratch2);
1359  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == rcx, "ABI mismatch");
1360  __ Move(rcx, optimized_code_entry);
1361  __ JumpCodeObject(rcx, kJSEntrypointTag, jump_mode);
1362 
1363  // Optimized code slot contains deoptimized code or code is cleared and
1364  // optimized code marker isn't updated. Evict the code, update the marker
1365  // and re-enter the closure's code.
1366  __ bind(&heal_optimized_code_slot);
1367  __ GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kHealOptimizedCodeSlot, jump_mode);
1368 }
1369 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1370 
1371 } // namespace

1377  Assert(equal, AbortReason::kExpectedFeedbackCell);
1378  }
1379 }

1381  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
1382  IsObjectType(object, FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE, scratch);
1383  Assert(equal, AbortReason::kExpectedFeedbackVector);

1385 }

1387 
1388 void MacroAssembler::GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(
1389  Runtime::FunctionId function_id, JumpMode jump_mode) {
1390  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
1391  // -- rax : actual argument count (preserved for callee)
1392  // -- rdx : new target (preserved for callee)
1393  // -- rdi : target function (preserved for callee)
1394  // -- r15 : dispatch handle (preserved for callee)
1395  // -----------------------------------
1396  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1397  {
1398  FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
1399  // Push a copy of the target function, the new target, the actual argument
1400  // count, and the dispatch handle.
1401  Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
1402  Push(kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister);
1403  SmiTag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
1404  Push(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
1405 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
1406  // No need to SmiTag since dispatch handles always look like Smis.
1407  static_assert(kJSDispatchHandleShift > 0);
1408  AssertSmi(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
1409  Push(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
1410 #endif
1411  // Function is also the parameter to the runtime call.
1412  Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
1413 
1414  CallRuntime(function_id, 1);
1415 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1416  movq(rcx, rax);
1417 #endif
1418 
1419  // Restore target function, new target, actual argument count, and dispatch
1420  // handle.
1421 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
1422  Pop(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
1423 #endif
1424  Pop(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
1425  SmiUntagUnsigned(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
1426  Pop(kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister);
1427  Pop(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
1428  }
1429 
1430  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == rcx, "ABI mismatch");
1431 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1432 #ifndef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
1433  movl(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister,
1434  FieldOperand(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister,
1435  JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
1436 #endif
1437  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(rcx, kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
1438  DCHECK_EQ(jump_mode, JumpMode::kJump);
1439  jmp(rcx);
1440 #else
1441  JumpCodeObject(rcx, kJSEntrypointTag, jump_mode);
1442 #endif
1443 }
1444 
1445 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1446 
1447 void MacroAssembler::ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(
1448  Register optimized_code, Register closure, Register scratch1,
1449  Register slot_address) {
1450  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1451  DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code, closure, scratch1, slot_address));
1452  DCHECK_EQ(closure, kJSFunctionRegister);
1453 
1454  // Store the optimized code in the closure.
1455  AssertCode(optimized_code);
1456  StoreCodePointerField(FieldOperand(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset),
1457  optimized_code);
1458 
1459  // Write barrier clobbers scratch1 below.
1460  Register value = scratch1;
1461  movq(value, optimized_code);
1462 
1463  RecordWriteField(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset, value, slot_address,
1464  SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore, SmiCheck::kOmit,
1465  ReadOnlyCheck::kOmit, SlotDescriptor::ForCodePointerSlot());
1466 }
1467 
1468 // Read off the flags in the feedback vector and check if there
1469 // is optimized code or a tiering state that needs to be processed.
1470 Condition MacroAssembler::CheckFeedbackVectorFlagsNeedsProcessing(
1471  Register feedback_vector, CodeKind current_code_kind) {
1472  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1473  DCHECK(CodeKindCanTierUp(current_code_kind));
1474  uint32_t flag_mask =
1475  FeedbackVector::FlagMaskForNeedsProcessingCheckFrom(current_code_kind);
1476  testw(FieldOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset),
1477  Immediate(flag_mask));
1478  return not_zero;
1479 }
1480 
1481 void MacroAssembler::CheckFeedbackVectorFlagsAndJumpIfNeedsProcessing(
1482  Register feedback_vector, CodeKind current_code_kind,
1483  Label* flags_need_processing) {
1484  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1485  j(CheckFeedbackVectorFlagsNeedsProcessing(feedback_vector, current_code_kind),
1486  flags_need_processing);
1487 }
1488 
1489 void MacroAssembler::OptimizeCodeOrTailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(
1490  Register feedback_vector, Register closure, JumpMode jump_mode) {
1491  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1492  DCHECK(!AreAliased(feedback_vector, closure));
1493 
1494  Label maybe_has_optimized_code, maybe_needs_logging;
1495  // Check if optimized code is available.
1496  testw(FieldOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset),
1497  Immediate(FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested));
1498  j(zero, &maybe_needs_logging);
1499 
1500  GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kCompileOptimized, jump_mode);
1501 
1502  bind(&maybe_needs_logging);
1503  testw(FieldOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset),
1504  Immediate(FeedbackVector::LogNextExecutionBit::kMask));
1505  j(zero, &maybe_has_optimized_code);
1506  GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kFunctionLogNextExecution, jump_mode);
1507 
1508  bind(&maybe_has_optimized_code);
1509  Register optimized_code_entry = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
1510  LoadTaggedField(
1511  optimized_code_entry,
1512  FieldOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kMaybeOptimizedCodeOffset));
1513  TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(this, optimized_code_entry, closure, r9,
1514  WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister(),
1515  jump_mode);
1516 }

1520 int MacroAssembler::RequiredStackSizeForCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
1521  Register exclusion) const {
1522  int bytes = 0;
1523  RegList saved_regs = kCallerSaved - exclusion;
1524  bytes += kSystemPointerSize * saved_regs.Count();
1525 
1526  // R12 to r15 are callee save on all platforms.
1527  if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
1528  bytes += kStackSavedSavedFPSize * kAllocatableDoubleRegisters.Count();
1529  }
1530 
1531  return bytes;
1532 }
1533 
1534 int MacroAssembler::PushCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
1535  Register exclusion) {
1536  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1537  int bytes = 0;
1538  bytes += PushAll(kCallerSaved - exclusion);
1539  if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
1540  bytes += PushAll(kAllocatableDoubleRegisters);
1541  }
1542 
1543  return bytes;
1544 }
1545 
1546 int MacroAssembler::PopCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, Register exclusion) {
1547  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1548  int bytes = 0;
1549  if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
1550  bytes += PopAll(kAllocatableDoubleRegisters);
1551  }
1552  bytes += PopAll(kCallerSaved - exclusion);
1553 
1554  return bytes;
1555 }
1556 
1557 int MacroAssembler::PushAll(RegList registers) {
1558  int bytes = 0;
1559  for (Register reg : registers) {
1560  pushq(reg);
1561  bytes += kSystemPointerSize;
1562  }
1563  return bytes;
1564 }
1565 
1566 int MacroAssembler::PopAll(RegList registers) {
1567  int bytes = 0;
1568  for (Register reg : base::Reversed(registers)) {
1569  popq(reg);
1570  bytes += kSystemPointerSize;
1571  }
1572  return bytes;
1573 }
1574 
1575 int MacroAssembler::PushAll(DoubleRegList registers, int stack_slot_size) {
1576  if (registers.is_empty()) return 0;
1577  const int delta = stack_slot_size * registers.Count();
1578  AllocateStackSpace(delta);
1579  int slot = 0;
1580  for (XMMRegister reg : registers) {
1581  if (stack_slot_size == kDoubleSize) {
1582  Movsd(Operand(rsp, slot), reg);
1583  } else {
1584  DCHECK_EQ(stack_slot_size, 2 * kDoubleSize);
1585  Movdqu(Operand(rsp, slot), reg);
1586  }
1587  slot += stack_slot_size;
1588  }
1589  DCHECK_EQ(slot, delta);
1590  return delta;
1591 }
1592 
1593 int MacroAssembler::PopAll(DoubleRegList registers, int stack_slot_size) {
1594  if (registers.is_empty()) return 0;
1595  int slot = 0;
1596  for (XMMRegister reg : registers) {
1597  if (stack_slot_size == kDoubleSize) {
1598  Movsd(reg, Operand(rsp, slot));
1599  } else {
1600  DCHECK_EQ(stack_slot_size, 2 * kDoubleSize);
1601  Movdqu(reg, Operand(rsp, slot));
1602  }
1603  slot += stack_slot_size;
1604  }
1605  DCHECK_EQ(slot, stack_slot_size * registers.Count());
1606  addq(rsp, Immediate(slot));
1607  return slot;
1608 }

1778 void MacroAssembler::Cvtqui2ss(XMMRegister dst, Register src) {
1779  Label done;
1780  Cvtqsi2ss(dst, src);
1781  testq(src, src);
1782  j(positive, &done, Label::kNear);
1783 
1784  // Compute {src/2 | (src&1)} (retain the LSB to avoid rounding errors).
1785  if (src != kScratchRegister) movq(kScratchRegister, src);
1786  shrq(kScratchRegister, Immediate(1));
1787  // The LSB is shifted into CF. If it is set, set the LSB in {tmp}.
1788  Label msb_not_set;
1789  j(not_carry, &msb_not_set, Label::kNear);
1790  orq(kScratchRegister, Immediate(1));
1791  bind(&msb_not_set);
1792  Cvtqsi2ss(dst, kScratchRegister);
1793  Addss(dst, dst);
1794  bind(&done);
1795 }
1796 
1797 void MacroAssembler::Cvtqui2ss(XMMRegister dst, Operand src) {
1798  movq(kScratchRegister, src);
1799  Cvtqui2ss(dst, kScratchRegister);
1800 }
1801 
1802 void MacroAssembler::Cvtqui2sd(XMMRegister dst, Register src) {
1803  Label done;
1804  Cvtqsi2sd(dst, src);
1805  testq(src, src);
1806  j(positive, &done, Label::kNear);
1807 
1808  // Compute {src/2 | (src&1)} (retain the LSB to avoid rounding errors).
1809  if (src != kScratchRegister) movq(kScratchRegister, src);
1810  shrq(kScratchRegister, Immediate(1));
1811  // The LSB is shifted into CF. If it is set, set the LSB in {tmp}.
1812  Label msb_not_set;
1813  j(not_carry, &msb_not_set, Label::kNear);
1814  orq(kScratchRegister, Immediate(1));
1815  bind(&msb_not_set);
1816  Cvtqsi2sd(dst, kScratchRegister);
1817  Addsd(dst, dst);
1818  bind(&done);
1819 }
1820 
1821 void MacroAssembler::Cvtqui2sd(XMMRegister dst, Operand src) {
1822  movq(kScratchRegister, src);
1823  Cvtqui2sd(dst, kScratchRegister);
1824 }

1898 void MacroAssembler::Cvtph2pd(XMMRegister dst, XMMRegister src) {
1899  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1900  CpuFeatureScope f16c_scope(this, F16C);
1901  CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
1902 
1903  vcvtph2ps(dst, src);
1904  Cvtss2sd(dst, dst);
1905 }
1906 
1907 void MacroAssembler::Cvtpd2ph(XMMRegister dst, XMMRegister src, Register tmp) {
1908  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1909  CpuFeatureScope f16c_scope(this, F16C);
1910  CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
1911  Register tmp2 = kScratchRegister;
1912  DCHECK_NE(tmp, tmp2);
1913  DCHECK_NE(dst, src);
1914 
1915  // Conversion algo from
1916  // https://github.com/tc39/proposal-float16array/issues/12#issuecomment-2256642971
1917  Label f32tof16;
1918  // Convert Float64 -> Float32.
1919  Cvtsd2ss(dst, src);
1920  vmovd(tmp, dst);
1921  // Mask off sign bit.
1922  andl(tmp, Immediate(kFP32WithoutSignMask));
1923  // Underflow to zero.
1924  cmpl(tmp, Immediate(kFP32MinFP16ZeroRepresentable));
1925  j(below, &f32tof16);
1926  // Overflow to infinity.
1927  cmpl(tmp, Immediate(kFP32MaxFP16Representable));
1928  j(above_equal, &f32tof16);
1929  // Detection of subnormal numbers.
1930  cmpl(tmp, Immediate(kFP32SubnormalThresholdOfFP16));
1931  setcc(above_equal, tmp2);
1932  movzxbl(tmp2, tmp2);
1933  // Compute 0x1000 for normal and 0x0000 for denormal numbers.
1934  shll(tmp2, Immediate(12));
1935  // Look at the last thirteen bits of the mantissa which will be shifted out
1936  // when converting from float32 to float16. (The round and sticky bits.)
1937  // Normal numbers: If the round bit is set and sticky bits are zero, then
1938  // adjust the float32 mantissa.
1939  // Denormal numbers: If all bits are zero, then adjust the mantissa.
1940  andl(tmp, Immediate(0x1fff));
1941  // Check round and sticky bits.
1942  cmpl(tmp, tmp2);
1943  j(not_equal, &f32tof16);
1944 
1945  // Adjust mantissa by -1/0/+1.
1946  Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<uint32_t>(1));
1947  psignd(kScratchDoubleReg, src);
1948  paddd(dst, kScratchDoubleReg);
1949 
1950  bind(&f32tof16);
1951  // Convert Float32 -> Float16.
1952  vcvtps2ph(dst, dst, 4);
1953 }
1954 
1955 namespace {
1956 template <typename OperandOrXMMRegister, bool is_double>
1957 void ConvertFloatToUint64(MacroAssembler* masm, Register dst,
1958  OperandOrXMMRegister src, Label* fail) {
1959  Label success;
1960  // There does not exist a native float-to-uint instruction, so we have to use
1961  // a float-to-int, and postprocess the result.
1962  if (is_double) {
1963  masm->Cvttsd2siq(dst, src);
1964  } else {
1965  masm->Cvttss2siq(dst, src);
1966  }
1967  // If the result of the conversion is positive, we are already done.
1968  masm->testq(dst, dst);
1969  masm->j(positive, &success);
1970  // The result of the first conversion was negative, which means that the
1971  // input value was not within the positive int64 range. We subtract 2^63
1972  // and convert it again to see if it is within the uint64 range.
1973  if (is_double) {
1974  masm->Move(kScratchDoubleReg, -9223372036854775808.0);
1975  masm->Addsd(kScratchDoubleReg, src);
1976  masm->Cvttsd2siq(dst, kScratchDoubleReg);
1977  } else {
1978  masm->Move(kScratchDoubleReg, -9223372036854775808.0f);
1979  masm->Addss(kScratchDoubleReg, src);
1980  masm->Cvttss2siq(dst, kScratchDoubleReg);
1981  }
1982  masm->testq(dst, dst);
1983  // The only possible negative value here is 0x8000000000000000, which is
1984  // used on x64 to indicate an integer overflow.
1985  masm->j(negative, fail ? fail : &success);
1986  // The input value is within uint64 range and the second conversion worked
1987  // successfully, but we still have to undo the subtraction we did
1988  // earlier.
1989  masm->Move(kScratchRegister, 0x8000000000000000);
1990  masm->orq(dst, kScratchRegister);
1991  masm->bind(&success);
1992 }
1993 
1994 template <typename OperandOrXMMRegister, bool is_double>
1995 void ConvertFloatToUint32(MacroAssembler* masm, Register dst,
1996  OperandOrXMMRegister src, Label* fail) {
1997  Label success;
1998  // There does not exist a native float-to-uint instruction, so we have to use
1999  // a float-to-int, and postprocess the result.
2000  if (is_double) {
2001  masm->Cvttsd2si(dst, src);
2002  } else {
2003  masm->Cvttss2si(dst, src);
2004  }
2005  // If the result of the conversion is positive, we are already done.
2006  masm->testl(dst, dst);
2007  masm->j(positive, &success);
2008  // The result of the first conversion was negative, which means that the
2009  // input value was not within the positive int32 range. We subtract 2^31
2010  // and convert it again to see if it is within the uint32 range.
2011  if (is_double) {
2012  masm->Move(kScratchDoubleReg, -2147483648.0);
2013  masm->Addsd(kScratchDoubleReg, src);
2014  masm->Cvttsd2si(dst, kScratchDoubleReg);
2015  } else {
2016  masm->Move(kScratchDoubleReg, -2147483648.0f);
2017  masm->Addss(kScratchDoubleReg, src);
2018  masm->Cvttss2si(dst, kScratchDoubleReg);
2019  }
2020  masm->testl(dst, dst);
2021  // The only possible negative value here is 0x80000000, which is
2022  // used on x64 to indicate an integer overflow.
2023  masm->j(negative, fail ? fail : &success);
2024  // The input value is within uint32 range and the second conversion worked
2025  // successfully, but we still have to undo the subtraction we did
2026  // earlier.
2027  masm->Move(kScratchRegister, 0x80000000);
2028  masm->orl(dst, kScratchRegister);
2029  masm->bind(&success);
2030 }

2083 void MacroAssembler::S256Not(YMMRegister dst, YMMRegister src,
2084  YMMRegister scratch) {

2087  if (dst == src) {
2088  vpcmpeqd(scratch, scratch, scratch);
2089  vpxor(dst, dst, scratch);
2090  } else {

2093  }

2096 void MacroAssembler::S256Select(YMMRegister dst, YMMRegister mask,
2097  YMMRegister src1, YMMRegister src2,
2098  YMMRegister scratch) {
2099  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2100  CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2101  // v256.select = v256.or(v256.and(v1, c), v256.andnot(v2, c)).
2102  // pandn(x, y) = !x & y, so we have to flip the mask and input.
2103  vpandn(scratch, mask, src2);
2104  vpand(dst, src1, mask);
2105  vpor(dst, dst, scratch);
2106 }

2116 void MacroAssembler::Cmp(Register dst, int32_t src) {

2124 void MacroAssembler::I64x4Mul(YMMRegister dst, YMMRegister lhs, YMMRegister rhs,
2125  YMMRegister tmp1, YMMRegister tmp2) {
2126  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2127  DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst, tmp1, tmp2));
2128  DCHECK(!AreAliased(lhs, tmp1, tmp2));
2129  DCHECK(!AreAliased(rhs, tmp1, tmp2));
2130  DCHECK(CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX2));
2131  CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX2);
2132  // 1. Multiply high dword of each qword of left with right.
2133  vpsrlq(tmp1, lhs, uint8_t{32});
2134  vpmuludq(tmp1, tmp1, rhs);
2135  // 2. Multiply high dword of each qword of right with left.
2136  vpsrlq(tmp2, rhs, uint8_t{32});
2137  vpmuludq(tmp2, tmp2, lhs);
2138  // 3. Add 1 and 2, then shift left by 32 (this is the high dword of result).
2139  vpaddq(tmp2, tmp2, tmp1);
2140  vpsllq(tmp2, tmp2, uint8_t{32});
2141  // 4. Multiply low dwords (this is the low dword of result).
2142  vpmuludq(dst, lhs, rhs);
2143  // 5. Add 3 and 4.
2144  vpaddq(dst, dst, tmp2);
2145 }

2244 void MacroAssembler::F16x8Min(YMMRegister dst, XMMRegister lhs, XMMRegister rhs,
2245  YMMRegister scratch, YMMRegister scratch2) {
2246  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2247  CpuFeatureScope f16c_scope(this, F16C);
2248  CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
2249  CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2250  vcvtph2ps(scratch, lhs);
2251  vcvtph2ps(scratch2, rhs);
2252  // The minps instruction doesn't propagate NaNs and +0's in its first
2253  // operand. Perform minps in both orders, merge the results, and adjust.
2254  vminps(dst, scratch, scratch2);
2255  vminps(scratch, scratch2, scratch);
2256  // Propagate -0's and NaNs, which may be non-canonical.
2257  vorps(scratch, scratch, dst);
2258  // Canonicalize NaNs by quieting and clearing the payload.
2259  vcmpunordps(dst, dst, scratch);
2260  vorps(scratch, scratch, dst);
2261  vpsrld(dst, dst, uint8_t{10});
2262  vandnps(dst, dst, scratch);
2263  vcvtps2ph(dst, dst, 0);
2264 }
2265 
2266 void MacroAssembler::F16x8Max(YMMRegister dst, XMMRegister lhs, XMMRegister rhs,
2267  YMMRegister scratch, YMMRegister scratch2) {
2268  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2269  CpuFeatureScope f16c_scope(this, F16C);
2270  CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
2271  CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2272  vcvtph2ps(scratch, lhs);
2273  vcvtph2ps(scratch2, rhs);
2274  // The maxps instruction doesn't propagate NaNs and +0's in its first
2275  // operand. Perform maxps in both orders, merge the results, and adjust.
2276  vmaxps(dst, scratch, scratch2);
2277  vmaxps(scratch, scratch2, scratch);
2278  // Find discrepancies.
2279  vxorps(dst, dst, scratch);
2280  // Propagate NaNs, which may be non-canonical.
2281  vorps(scratch, scratch, dst);
2282  // Propagate sign discrepancy and (subtle) quiet NaNs.
2283  vsubps(scratch, scratch, dst);
2284  // Canonicalize NaNs by clearing the payload. Sign is non-deterministic.
2285  vcmpunordps(dst, dst, scratch);
2286  vpsrld(dst, dst, uint8_t{10});
2287  vandnps(dst, dst, scratch);
2288  vcvtps2ph(dst, dst, 0);
2289 }

2291 // 1. Zero extend 4 packed 32-bit integers in src1 to 4 packed 64-bit integers
2292 // in scratch
2293 // 2. Zero extend 4 packed 32-bit integers in src2 to 4 packed 64-bit integers
2294 // in dst
2295 // 3. Multiply packed doubleword integers in scratch with dst, the extended zero
2296 // are ignored
2297 void MacroAssembler::I64x4ExtMul(YMMRegister dst, XMMRegister src1,
2298  XMMRegister src2, YMMRegister scratch,
2299  bool is_signed) {
2300  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2301  DCHECK(CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX2));
2302  CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX2);
2303  vpmovzxdq(scratch, src1);
2304  vpmovzxdq(dst, src2);
2305  if (is_signed) {
2306  vpmuldq(dst, scratch, dst);
2307  } else {
2308  vpmuludq(dst, scratch, dst);
2309  }
2310 }
2311 
2312 // 1. Extend 8 packed 16-bit integers in src1 to 8 packed 32-bit integers in
2313 // scratch
2314 // 2. Extend 8 packed 16-bit integers in src2 to 8 packed 32-bit integers in dst
2315 // 3. Multiply the packed doubleword integers in scratch and dst and store the
2316 // low 32 bits of each product in dst.
2317 void MacroAssembler::I32x8ExtMul(YMMRegister dst, XMMRegister src1,
2318  XMMRegister src2, YMMRegister scratch,
2319  bool is_signed) {
2320  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2321  DCHECK(CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX2));

2324  is_signed ? vpmovsxwd(dst, src2) : vpmovzxwd(dst, src2);
2325  vpmulld(dst, dst, scratch);
2326 }

2339 void MacroAssembler::I32x8ExtAddPairwiseI16x16S(YMMRegister dst,

2341  YMMRegister scratch) {

2394 void MacroAssembler::I32x8SConvertF32x8(YMMRegister dst, YMMRegister src,
2395  YMMRegister tmp, Register scratch) {
2396  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2397  DCHECK(CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) && CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX2));
2398  CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
2399  CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2400  Operand int32_overflow_as_float = ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
2401  ExternalReference::address_of_wasm_i32x8_int32_overflow_as_float(),
2402  scratch);
2403  // This algorithm works by:
2404  // 1. lanes with NaNs are zero-ed
2405  // 2. lanes ge than 2147483648.0f (MAX_INT32+1) set to 0xffff'ffff
2406  // 3. cvttps2dq sets all out of range lanes to 0x8000'0000
2407  // a. correct for underflows (< MIN_INT32)
2408  // b. wrong for overflow, and we know which lanes overflow from 2.
2409  // 4. adjust for 3b by xor-ing 2 and 3
2410  // a. 0x8000'0000 xor 0xffff'ffff = 0x7fff'ffff (MAX_INT32)
2411  vcmpeqps(tmp, src, src);
2412  vandps(dst, src, tmp);
2413  vcmpgeps(tmp, src, int32_overflow_as_float);
2414  vcvttps2dq(dst, dst);
2415  vpxor(dst, dst, tmp);
2416 }
2417 
2418 void MacroAssembler::I16x8SConvertF16x8(YMMRegister dst, XMMRegister src,
2419  YMMRegister tmp, Register scratch) {
2420  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2421  DCHECK(CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) && CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX2) &&
2422  CpuFeatures::IsSupported(F16C));
2423 
2424  CpuFeatureScope f16c_scope(this, F16C);
2425  CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
2426  CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2427 
2428  Operand op = ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
2429  ExternalReference::address_of_wasm_i32x8_int32_overflow_as_float(),
2430  scratch);
2431  // Convert source f16 to f32.
2432  vcvtph2ps(dst, src);
2433  // Compare it to itself, NaNs are turn to 0s because don't equal to itself.
2434  vcmpeqps(tmp, dst, dst);
2435  // Reset NaNs.
2436  vandps(dst, dst, tmp);
2437  // Detect positive Infinity as an overflow above MAX_INT32.
2438  vcmpgeps(tmp, dst, op);
2439  // Convert f32 to i32.
2440  vcvttps2dq(dst, dst);
2441  // cvttps2dq sets all out of range lanes to 0x8000'0000,
2442  // but as soon as source values are result of conversion from f16,
2443  // and so less than MAX_INT32, only +Infinity is an issue.
2444  // Convert all infinities to MAX_INT32 and let vpackssdw
2445  // clamp it to MAX_INT16 later.
2446  // 0x8000'0000 xor 0xffff'ffff(from 2 steps before) = 0x7fff'ffff (MAX_INT32)
2447  vpxor(dst, dst, tmp);
2448  // We now have 8 i32 values. Using one character per 16 bits:
2449  // dst: [AABBCCDDEEFFGGHH]
2450  // Create a copy of the upper four values in the lower half of {tmp}
2451  // (so the upper half of the immediate doesn't matter):
2452  vpermq(tmp, dst, 0x4E); // 0b01001110
2453  // tmp: [EEFFGGHHAABBCCDD]
2454  // Now pack them together as i16s. Note that {vpackssdw} interleaves
2455  // 128-bit chunks from each input, and takes care of saturating each
2456  // value to kMinInt16 and kMaxInt16. We will then ignore the upper half
2457  // of {dst}.
2458  vpackssdw(dst, dst, tmp);
2459  // dst: [EFGHABCDABCDEFGH]
2460  // <--><--><--><-->
2461  // ↑ ↑ ↑ └── from lower half of {dst}
2462  // │ │ └────── from lower half of {tmp}
2463  // │ └────────── from upper half of {dst} (ignored)
2464  // └────────────── from upper half of {tmp} (ignored)
2465 }
2466 
2467 void MacroAssembler::I16x8TruncF16x8U(YMMRegister dst, XMMRegister src,
2468  YMMRegister tmp) {
2469  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2470  DCHECK(CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) && CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX2) &&
2471  CpuFeatures::IsSupported(F16C));
2472 
2473  CpuFeatureScope f16c_scope(this, F16C);
2474  CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
2475  CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2476 
2477  Operand op = ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
2478  ExternalReference::address_of_wasm_i32x8_int32_overflow_as_float(),
2479  kScratchRegister);
2480  vcvtph2ps(dst, src);
2481  // NAN->0, negative->0.
2482  vpxor(tmp, tmp, tmp);
2483  vmaxps(dst, dst, tmp);
2484  // Detect positive Infinity as an overflow above MAX_INT32.
2485  vcmpgeps(tmp, dst, op);
2486  // Convert to int.
2487  vcvttps2dq(dst, dst);
2488  // cvttps2dq sets all out of range lanes to 0x8000'0000,
2489  // but as soon as source values are result of conversion from f16,
2490  // and so less than MAX_INT32, only +Infinity is an issue.
2491  // Convert all infinities to MAX_INT32 and let vpackusdw
2492  // clamp it to MAX_INT16 later.
2493  // 0x8000'0000 xor 0xffff'ffff(from 2 steps before) = 0x7fff'ffff (MAX_INT32)
2494  vpxor(dst, dst, tmp);
2495  // Move high part to a spare register.
2496  // See detailed comment in {I16x8SConvertF16x8} for how this works.
2497  vpermq(tmp, dst, 0x4E); // 0b01001110
2498  vpackusdw(dst, dst, tmp);
2499 }

2501 void MacroAssembler::F16x8Qfma(YMMRegister dst, XMMRegister src1,
2502  XMMRegister src2, XMMRegister src3,
2503  YMMRegister tmp, YMMRegister tmp2) {
2504  CpuFeatureScope fma3_scope(this, FMA3);
2505  CpuFeatureScope f16c_scope(this, F16C);
2506 
2507  if (dst.code() == src2.code()) {
2508  vcvtph2ps(dst, dst);
2509  vcvtph2ps(tmp, src1);
2510  vcvtph2ps(tmp2, src3);
2511  vfmadd213ps(dst, tmp, tmp2);
2512  } else if (dst.code() == src3.code()) {
2513  vcvtph2ps(dst, dst);
2514  vcvtph2ps(tmp, src2);
2515  vcvtph2ps(tmp2, src1);
2516  vfmadd231ps(dst, tmp, tmp2);
2517  } else {
2518  vcvtph2ps(dst, src1);
2519  vcvtph2ps(tmp, src2);
2520  vcvtph2ps(tmp2, src3);
2521  vfmadd213ps(dst, tmp, tmp2);
2522  }
2523  vcvtps2ph(dst, dst, 0);
2524 }

2528  YMMRegister tmp, YMMRegister tmp2) {
2529  CpuFeatureScope fma3_scope(this, FMA3);
2530  CpuFeatureScope f16c_scope(this, F16C);
2531

2533  vcvtph2ps(dst, dst);
2534  vcvtph2ps(tmp, src1);
2535  vcvtph2ps(tmp2, src3);
2536  vfnmadd213ps(dst, tmp, tmp2);
2537  } else if (dst.code() == src3.code()) {
2538  vcvtph2ps(dst, dst);
2539  vcvtph2ps(tmp, src2);
2540  vcvtph2ps(tmp2, src1);
2541  vfnmadd231ps(dst, tmp, tmp2);

2575 void MacroAssembler::I32x8DotI8x32I7x32AddS(YMMRegister dst, YMMRegister src1,
2576  YMMRegister src2, YMMRegister src3,
2577  YMMRegister scratch,
2578  YMMRegister splat_reg) {
2579  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2580  DCHECK(CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) && CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX2));
2581  // It's guaranteed in instruction selector
2582  DCHECK_EQ(dst, src3);
2583  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX_VNNI_INT8)) {
2584  CpuFeatureScope avx_vnni_int8_scope(this, AVX_VNNI_INT8);
2585  vpdpbssd(dst, src2, src1);
2586  return;
2587  } else if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX_VNNI)) {
2588  CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX_VNNI);
2589  vpdpbusd(dst, src2, src1);
2590  return;
2591  }
2592 
2593  DCHECK_NE(scratch, splat_reg);
2594  CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
2595  CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2596  // splat_reg = i16x16.splat(1)
2597  vpcmpeqd(splat_reg, splat_reg, splat_reg);
2598  vpsrlw(splat_reg, splat_reg, uint8_t{15});
2599  vpmaddubsw(scratch, src2, src1);
2600  vpmaddwd(scratch, splat_reg, scratch);
2601  vpaddd(dst, src3, scratch);
2602 }

2604 void MacroAssembler::I32x8TruncF32x8U(YMMRegister dst, YMMRegister src,
2605  YMMRegister scratch1,
2606  YMMRegister scratch2) {
2607  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2608  DCHECK(CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) && CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX2));
2609  CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
2610  CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2611 
2612  // NAN->0, negative->0.
2613  vpxor(scratch1, scratch1, scratch1);
2614  vmaxps(dst, src, scratch1);
2615  // scratch1: float representation of max_signed.
2616  vpcmpeqd(scratch1, scratch1, scratch1);
2617  vpsrld(scratch1, scratch1, uint8_t{1}); // 0x7fffffff
2618  vcvtdq2ps(scratch1, scratch1); // 0x4f000000
2619  // scratch2: convert (src-max_signed).
2620  // Set positive overflow lanes to 0x7FFFFFFF.
2621  // Set negative lanes to 0.
2622  vsubps(scratch2, dst, scratch1);
2623 
2624  vcmpleps(scratch1, scratch1, scratch2);
2625  vcvttps2dq(scratch2, scratch2);
2626  vpxor(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
2627  vpxor(scratch1, scratch1, scratch1);
2628  vpmaxsd(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
2629  // Convert to int. Overflow lanes above max_signed will be 0x80000000.
2630  vcvttps2dq(dst, dst);
2631  // Add (src-max_signed) for overflow lanes.
2632  vpaddd(dst, dst, scratch2);
2633 }

2635 void MacroAssembler::SmiTag(Register reg) {
2636  static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
2637  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits() || SmiValuesAre31Bits());
2638  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
2639  DCHECK_EQ(kSmiShift, 1);
2640  addl(reg, reg);
2641  } else {
2642  shlq(reg, Immediate(kSmiShift));
2643  }
2644 #ifdef ENABLE_SLOW_DCHECKS
2645  ClobberDecompressedSmiBits(reg);
2646 #endif
2647 }

2649 void MacroAssembler::SmiTag(Register dst, Register src) {
2650  DCHECK(dst != src);
2651  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
2652  movl(dst, src);
2653  } else {
2654  movq(dst, src);
2655  }
2656  SmiTag(dst);
2657 }

2659 void MacroAssembler::SmiUntag(Register reg) {
2660  static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
2661  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits() || SmiValuesAre31Bits());
2662  // TODO(v8:7703): Is there a way to avoid this sign extension when pointer
2663  // compression is enabled?
2664  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
2665  sarl(reg, Immediate(kSmiShift));
2666  movsxlq(reg, reg);
2667  } else {
2668  sarq(reg, Immediate(kSmiShift));
2669  }
2670 }

2675  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
2676  AssertSignedBitOfSmiIsZero(reg);
2677  shrl(reg, Immediate(kSmiShift));
2678  } else {
2679  shrq(reg, Immediate(kSmiShift));
2680  }
2681 }

2683 void MacroAssembler::SmiUntag(Register dst, Register src) {
2684  DCHECK(dst != src);
2685  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
2686  movsxlq(dst, src);
2687  } else {
2688  movq(dst, src);
2689  }

2691  // mov when pointer compression is enabled.
2692  static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
2693  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits() || SmiValuesAre31Bits());
2694  sarq(dst, Immediate(kSmiShift));
2695 }

2701  } else {
2702  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
2703  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
2704  movsxlq(dst, src);
2705  } else {
2706  movq(dst, src);
2707  }
2708  sarq(dst, Immediate(kSmiShift));
2709  }
2710 }

2720  AssertSignedBitOfSmiIsZero(dst);

2726  }

2799 void MacroAssembler::ClobberDecompressedSmiBits(Register src) {
2800 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
2801  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2802  static constexpr unsigned int clobber_mask = 0x515151;
2803  static constexpr int rot_to_unused =
2804  64 - kSmiShiftSize - kSmiTagSize - kSmiValueSize;
2805  rolq(src, Immediate(rot_to_unused));
2806  xorq(src, Immediate(clobber_mask));
2807  rorq(src, Immediate(rot_to_unused));
2808 #endif
2809 }

2835 void MacroAssembler::JumpIfNotSmi(Operand src, Label* on_not_smi,
2836  Label::Distance near_jump) {
2837  Condition smi = CheckSmi(src);
2838  j(NegateCondition(smi), on_not_smi, near_jump);
2839 }
2840 
2841 void MacroAssembler::SmiAddConstant(Operand dst, Tagged<Smi> constant) {
2842  if (constant.value() != 0) {
2843  if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
2844  addl(Operand(dst, kSmiShift / kBitsPerByte), Immediate(constant.value()));
2845  } else {
2846  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
2847  if (kTaggedSize == kInt64Size) {
2848  // Sign-extend value after addition
2849  movl(kScratchRegister, dst);
2850  addl(kScratchRegister, Immediate(constant));
2851  movsxlq(kScratchRegister, kScratchRegister);
2852  movq(dst, kScratchRegister);
2853  } else {
2854  DCHECK_EQ(kTaggedSize, kInt32Size);
2855  addl(dst, Immediate(constant));
2856  }
2857  }
2858  }
2859 }
2860 
2861 SmiIndex MacroAssembler::SmiToIndex(Register dst, Register src, int shift) {
2862  if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
2863  DCHECK(is_uint6(shift));
2864  // There is a possible optimization if shift is in the range 60-63, but that
2865  // will (and must) never happen.
2866  if (dst != src) {
2867  movq(dst, src);
2868  }
2869  if (shift < kSmiShift) {
2870  sarq(dst, Immediate(kSmiShift - shift));
2871  } else {
2872  shlq(dst, Immediate(shift - kSmiShift));
2873  }
2874  return SmiIndex(dst, times_1);
2875  } else {
2876  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
2877  // We have to sign extend the index register to 64-bit as the SMI might
2878  // be negative.
2879  movsxlq(dst, src);
2880  if (shift < kSmiShift) {
2881  sarq(dst, Immediate(kSmiShift - shift));
2882  } else if (shift != kSmiShift) {
2883  if (shift - kSmiShift <= static_cast<int>(times_8)) {
2884  return SmiIndex(dst, static_cast<ScaleFactor>(shift - kSmiShift));
2885  }
2886  shlq(dst, Immediate(shift - kSmiShift));
2887  }
2888  return SmiIndex(dst, times_1);
2889  }
2890 }
2891 
2892 void MacroAssembler::Switch(Register scratch, Register reg, int case_value_base,
2893  Label** labels, int num_labels) {
2894  Register table = scratch;
2895  Label fallthrough, jump_table;
2896  if (case_value_base != 0) {
2897  subq(reg, Immediate(case_value_base));
2898  }
2899  cmpq(reg, Immediate(num_labels));
2900  j(above_equal, &fallthrough);
2901  leaq(table, MemOperand(&jump_table));
2902 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CET_IBT
2903  // Add the notrack prefix to disable landing pad enforcement.
2904  jmp(MemOperand(table, reg, times_8, 0), /*notrack=*/true);
2905 #else
2906  jmp(MemOperand(table, reg, times_8, 0));
2907 #endif
2908  // Emit the jump table inline, under the assumption that it's not too big.
2909  Align(kSystemPointerSize);
2910  bind(&jump_table);
2911  for (int i = 0; i < num_labels; ++i) {
2912  dq(labels[i]);
2913  }
2914  bind(&fallthrough);
2915 }
2916 
2917 void MacroAssembler::Push(Tagged<Smi> source) {
2918  intptr_t smi = static_cast<intptr_t>(source.ptr());
2919  if (is_int32(smi)) {
2920  Push(Immediate(static_cast<int32_t>(smi)));
2921  return;
2922  }
2923  int first_byte_set = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros64(smi) / 8;
2924  int last_byte_set = (63 - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros64(smi)) / 8;
2925  if (first_byte_set == last_byte_set) {
2926  // This sequence has only 7 bytes, compared to the 12 bytes below.
2927  Push(Immediate(0));
2928  movb(Operand(rsp, first_byte_set),
2929  Immediate(static_cast<int8_t>(smi >> (8 * first_byte_set))));
2930  return;
2931  }
2932  Register constant = GetSmiConstant(source);
2933  Push(constant);
2934 }

2938 void MacroAssembler::Move(Register dst, Tagged<Smi> source) {
2939  static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
2940  int value = source.value();
2941  if (value == 0) {
2942  xorl(dst, dst);
2943  } else if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
2944  Move(dst, source.ptr(), RelocInfo::NO_INFO);
2945  } else {
2946  uint32_t uvalue = static_cast<uint32_t>(source.ptr());
2947  Move(dst, uvalue);
2948  }
2949 }

2953  movq(dst, Immediate(static_cast<int32_t>(x)));
2954  } else {
2955  Move(kScratchRegister, x);
2956  movq(dst, kScratchRegister);
2957  }
2958 }
