2960 void MacroAssembler::Move(Register dst, ExternalReference ext) {
2961  // TODO(jgruber,v8:8887): Also consider a root-relative load when generating
2962  // non-isolate-independent code. In many cases it might be cheaper than
2963  // embedding the relocatable value.
2964  if (root_array_available()) {
2965  if (ext.IsIsolateFieldId()) {
2966  leaq(dst, Operand(kRootRegister, ext.offset_from_root_register()));
2967  return;
2968  } else if (options().isolate_independent_code) {
2969  IndirectLoadExternalReference(dst, ext);
2970  return;
2971  }
2972  }
2973  // External references should not get created with IDs if
2974  // `!root_array_available()`.
2975  CHECK(!ext.IsIsolateFieldId());
2976  movq(dst, Immediate64(ext.address(), RelocInfo::EXTERNAL_REFERENCE));
2977 }

3000 void MacroAssembler::MovePair(Register dst0, Register src0, Register dst1,
3001  Register src1) {
3002  if (dst0 != src1) {
3003  // Normal case: Writing to dst0 does not destroy src1.
3004  Move(dst0, src0);
3005  Move(dst1, src1);
3006  } else if (dst1 != src0) {
3007  // Only dst0 and src1 are the same register,
3008  // but writing to dst1 does not destroy src0.
3009  Move(dst1, src1);
3010  Move(dst0, src0);
3011  } else {
3012  // dst0 == src1, and dst1 == src0, a swap is required:
3013  // dst0 \/ src0
3014  // dst1 /\ src1
3015  xchgq(dst0, dst1);
3016  }
3017 }

3019 void MacroAssembler::MoveNumber(Register dst, double value) {

3022  Move(dst, Smi::FromInt(smi));
3023  } else {
3024  movq_heap_number(dst, value);
3025  }

3028 void MacroAssembler::Move(XMMRegister dst, uint32_t src) {
3029  if (src == 0) {
3030  Xorps(dst, dst);
3031  } else {
3032  unsigned nlz = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros(src);
3033  unsigned ntz = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(src);
3034  unsigned pop = base::bits::CountPopulation(src);
3035  DCHECK_NE(0u, pop);
3036  if (pop + ntz + nlz == 32) {
3037  Pcmpeqd(dst, dst);
3038  if (ntz) Pslld(dst, static_cast<uint8_t>(ntz + nlz));
3039  if (nlz) Psrld(dst, static_cast<uint8_t>(nlz));
3040  } else {
3041  movl(kScratchRegister, Immediate(src));
3042  Movd(dst, kScratchRegister);
3043  }
3044  }
3045 }
3046 
3047 void MacroAssembler::Move(XMMRegister dst, uint64_t src) {
3048  if (src == 0) {
3049  Xorpd(dst, dst);
3050  } else {
3051  unsigned nlz = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros(src);
3052  unsigned ntz = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(src);
3053  unsigned pop = base::bits::CountPopulation(src);
3054  DCHECK_NE(0u, pop);
3055  if (pop + ntz + nlz == 64) {
3056  Pcmpeqd(dst, dst);
3057  if (ntz) Psllq(dst, static_cast<uint8_t>(ntz + nlz));
3058  if (nlz) Psrlq(dst, static_cast<uint8_t>(nlz));
3059  } else {
3060  uint32_t lower = static_cast<uint32_t>(src);
3061  uint32_t upper = static_cast<uint32_t>(src >> 32);
3062  if (upper == 0) {
3063  Move(dst, lower);
3064  } else {
3065  movq(kScratchRegister, src);
3066  Movq(dst, kScratchRegister);
3067  }
3068  }
3069  }
3070 }
3071 
3072 void MacroAssembler::Move(XMMRegister dst, uint64_t high, uint64_t low) {
3073  if (high == low) {
3074  Move(dst, low);
3075  Punpcklqdq(dst, dst);
3076  return;
3077  }
3078 
3079  Move(dst, low);
3080  movq(kScratchRegister, high);
3081  Pinsrq(dst, dst, kScratchRegister, uint8_t{1});
3082 }

3086 void MacroAssembler::Cmp(Register dst, Handle<Object> source) {
3087  if (IsSmi(*source)) {
3088  Cmp(dst, Cast<Smi>(*source));
3089  } else if (root_array_available_ && options().isolate_independent_code) {
3090  // TODO(jgruber,v8:8887): Also consider a root-relative load when generating
3091  // non-isolate-independent code. In many cases it might be cheaper than
3092  // embedding the relocatable value.
3093  // TODO(v8:9706): Fix-it! This load will always uncompress the value
3094  // even when we are loading a compressed embedded object.
3095  IndirectLoadConstant(kScratchRegister, Cast<HeapObject>(source));
3096  cmp_tagged(dst, kScratchRegister);
3097  } else if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
3098  EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(Cast<HeapObject>(source));
3099  DCHECK(is_uint32(index));
3100  cmpl(dst, Immediate(static_cast<int>(index),
3101  RelocInfo::COMPRESSED_EMBEDDED_OBJECT));
3102  } else {
3103  movq(kScratchRegister,
3104  Immediate64(source.address(), RelocInfo::FULL_EMBEDDED_OBJECT));
3105  cmpq(dst, kScratchRegister);
3106  }
3107 }

3132 void MacroAssembler::CompareRange(Register value, unsigned lower_limit,
3133  unsigned higher_limit) {
3134  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3135  DCHECK_LT(lower_limit, higher_limit);
3136  if (lower_limit != 0) {
3137  leal(kScratchRegister, Operand(value, 0u - lower_limit));
3138  cmpl(kScratchRegister, Immediate(higher_limit - lower_limit));
3139  } else {
3140  cmpl(value, Immediate(higher_limit));
3141  }

3156 void MacroAssembler::PushArray(Register array, Register size, Register scratch,
3157  PushArrayOrder order) {
3158  DCHECK(!AreAliased(array, size, scratch));
3159  Register counter = scratch;
3160  Label loop, entry;
3161  if (order == PushArrayOrder::kReverse) {
3162  Move(counter, 0);
3163  jmp(&entry);
3164  bind(&loop);
3165  Push(Operand(array, counter, times_system_pointer_size, 0));
3166  incq(counter);
3167  bind(&entry);
3168  cmpq(counter, size);
3169  j(less, &loop, Label::kNear);
3170  } else {
3171  movq(counter, size);
3172  jmp(&entry);
3173  bind(&loop);
3174  Push(Operand(array, counter, times_system_pointer_size, 0));
3175  bind(&entry);
3176  decq(counter);
3177  j(greater_equal, &loop, Label::kNear);
3178  }
3179 }

3182  RelocInfo::Mode rmode) {
3183  // TODO(jgruber,v8:8887): Also consider a root-relative load when generating
3184  // non-isolate-independent code. In many cases it might be cheaper than
3185  // embedding the relocatable value.
3186  if (root_array_available_ && options().isolate_independent_code) {

3188  // even when we are loading a compressed embedded object.

3367 Operand MacroAssembler::EntryFromBuiltinIndexAsOperand(Register builtin_index) {
3368  if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
3369  // The builtin_index register contains the builtin index as a Smi.
3370  Move(kScratchRegister, builtin_index); // Callee checks for equality.
3371  SmiUntagUnsigned(kScratchRegister);
3372  return Operand(kRootRegister, kScratchRegister, times_system_pointer_size,
3373  IsolateData::builtin_entry_table_offset());
3374  } else {
3375  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
3376 
3377  // The builtin_index register contains the builtin index as a Smi.
3378  // Untagging is folded into the indexing operand below (we use
3379  // times_half_system_pointer_size since smis are already shifted by one).
3380  return Operand(kRootRegister, builtin_index, times_half_system_pointer_size,
3381  IsolateData::builtin_entry_table_offset());
3382  }
3383 }

3390 void MacroAssembler::CallBuiltin(Builtin builtin) {
3391  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, CommentForOffHeapTrampoline("call", builtin));
3392 
3393  // Check if this builtin call transitions out of sandboxed execution mode.
3394  SwitchSandboxingModeBeforeCallIfNeeded(Builtins::SandboxingModeOf(builtin));
3395 
3396  switch (options().builtin_call_jump_mode) {
3397  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kAbsolute:
3398  Call(BuiltinEntry(builtin), RelocInfo::OFF_HEAP_TARGET);
3399  break;
3400  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:
3401  near_call(static_cast<intptr_t>(builtin), RelocInfo::NEAR_BUILTIN_ENTRY);
3402  break;
3403  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect:
3404  Call(EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(builtin));
3405  break;
3406  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {
3407  Handle<Code> code = isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
3408  call(code, RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
3409  break;
3410  }
3411  }
3412 
3413  SwitchSandboxingModeAfterCallIfNeeded(Builtins::SandboxingModeOf(builtin));
3414 }
3415 
3416 void MacroAssembler::TailCallBuiltin(Builtin builtin) {
3417  // We cannot (currently) switch the sandboxing mode on tail calls.
3418  DCHECK_EQ(sandboxing_mode(), Builtins::SandboxingModeOf(builtin));
3419 
3420  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this,
3421  CommentForOffHeapTrampoline("tail call", builtin));
3422  switch (options().builtin_call_jump_mode) {
3423  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kAbsolute:
3424  Jump(BuiltinEntry(builtin), RelocInfo::OFF_HEAP_TARGET);
3425  break;
3426  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:
3427  near_jmp(static_cast<intptr_t>(builtin), RelocInfo::NEAR_BUILTIN_ENTRY);
3428  break;
3429  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect:
3430  Jump(EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(builtin));
3431  break;
3432  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {
3433  Handle<Code> code = isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
3434  jmp(code, RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
3435  break;
3436  }
3437  }
3438 }
3439 
3440 void MacroAssembler::TailCallBuiltin(Builtin builtin, Condition cc) {
3441  // We cannot (currently) switch the sandboxing mode on tail calls.
3442  DCHECK_EQ(sandboxing_mode(), Builtins::SandboxingModeOf(builtin));
3443 
3444  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this,
3445  CommentForOffHeapTrampoline("tail call", builtin));
3446  switch (options().builtin_call_jump_mode) {
3447  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kAbsolute:
3448  Jump(BuiltinEntry(builtin), RelocInfo::OFF_HEAP_TARGET, cc);
3449  break;
3450  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:
3451  near_j(cc, static_cast<intptr_t>(builtin), RelocInfo::NEAR_BUILTIN_ENTRY);
3452  break;
3453  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect:
3454  Jump(EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(builtin), cc);
3455  break;
3456  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {
3457  Handle<Code> code = isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
3458  j(cc, code, RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
3459  break;
3460  }
3461  }
3462 }

3464 void MacroAssembler::LoadCodeInstructionStart(Register destination,
3465  Register code_object,
3466  CodeEntrypointTag tag) {
3467  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3468 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
3469  LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(
3470  destination, FieldOperand(code_object, Code::kSelfIndirectPointerOffset),
3471  tag);
3472 #else
3473  movq(destination, FieldOperand(code_object, Code::kInstructionStartOffset));
3474 #endif
3475 }
3476 
3477 void MacroAssembler::CallCodeObject(Register code_object,
3478  CodeEntrypointTag tag) {
3479  LoadCodeInstructionStart(code_object, code_object, tag);
3480  call(code_object);
3481 }
3482 
3483 void MacroAssembler::JumpCodeObject(Register code_object, CodeEntrypointTag tag,
3484  JumpMode jump_mode) {
3485  // TODO(saelo): can we avoid using this for JavaScript functions
3486  // (kJSEntrypointTag) and instead use a variant that ensures that the caller
3487  // and callee agree on the signature (i.e. parameter count)?
3488  LoadCodeInstructionStart(code_object, code_object, tag);
3489  switch (jump_mode) {
3490  case JumpMode::kJump:
3491  jmp(code_object);
3492  return;
3493  case JumpMode::kPushAndReturn:
3494  pushq(code_object);
3495  Ret();
3496  return;
3497  }
3498 }
3499 
3500 void MacroAssembler::CallJSFunction(Register function_object,
3501  uint16_t argument_count) {
3502 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
3503  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == rcx, "ABI mismatch");
3504  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister == r15, "ABI mismatch");
3505  movl(r15, FieldOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
3506  LoadEntrypointAndParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(rcx, rbx, r15);
3507  // Force a safe crash if the parameter count doesn't match.
3508  // TODO(412398354): to avoid this runtime check, we should switch all
3509  // remaining users to call the function via its dispatch handle instead. See
3510  // CallJSDispatchEntry below and crbug.com/412398354 for more details.
3511  cmpl(rbx, Immediate(argument_count));
3512  SbxCheck(less_equal, AbortReason::kJSSignatureMismatch);
3513  call(rcx);
3514 #else
3515  CHECK(!V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
3516  LoadTaggedField(rcx, FieldOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
3517  CallCodeObject(rcx, kJSEntrypointTag);
3518 #endif
3519 }
3520 
3521 #if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
3522 void MacroAssembler::CallJSDispatchEntry(JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
3523  uint16_t argument_count) {
3524  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == rcx, "ABI mismatch");
3525  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister == r15, "ABI mismatch");
3526  movl(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister,
3527  Immediate(dispatch_handle.value(), RelocInfo::JS_DISPATCH_HANDLE));
3528  // WARNING: This entrypoint load is only safe because we are storing a
3529  // RelocInfo for the dispatch handle in the movl above (thus keeping the
3530  // dispatch entry alive) _and_ because the entrypoints are not compactable
3531  // (thus meaning that the calculation in the entrypoint load is not
3532  // invalidated by a compaction).
3533  // TODO(leszeks): Make this less of a footgun.
3534  static_assert(!JSDispatchTable::kSupportsCompaction);
3535  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(rcx, dispatch_handle);
3536  CHECK_EQ(argument_count,
3537  IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->GetParameterCount(
3538  dispatch_handle));
3539  call(rcx);
3540 }
3541 #endif
3542 
3543 void MacroAssembler::JumpJSFunction(Register function_object,
3544  JumpMode jump_mode) {
3545  CHECK(!V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
3546 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
3547  // This implementation is not currently used because callers usually need
3548  // to load both entry point and parameter count and then do something with
3549  // the latter before the actual call.
3550  UNREACHABLE();
3551 #else
3552  LoadTaggedField(rcx, FieldOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
3553  JumpCodeObject(rcx, kJSEntrypointTag, jump_mode);
3554 #endif
3555 }

3557 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3558 
3559 void MacroAssembler::CallWasmCodePointer(Register target,
3560  uint64_t signature_hash,
3561  CallJumpMode call_jump_mode) {
3562  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3563  Move(kScratchRegister, ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table());
3564 
3565 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
3566  static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == 16);
3567  // Check that using a 32-bit shift is valid for any valid code pointer.
3568  static_assert(wasm::WasmCodePointerTable::kMaxWasmCodePointers <=
3569  (kMaxInt >> 4));
3570  shll(target, Immediate(4));
3571  // Add `target` and `kScratchRegister` early to free `kScratchRegister` again.
3572  addq(target, kScratchRegister);
3573 
3574  Operand signature_hash_op{target,
3575  wasm::WasmCodePointerTable::kOffsetOfSignatureHash};
3576  if (is_int32(signature_hash)) {
3577  // cmpq sign-extends the 32-bit immediate.
3578  cmpq(signature_hash_op, Immediate(static_cast<int32_t>(signature_hash)));
3579  } else {
3580  Move(kScratchRegister, signature_hash);
3581  cmpq(kScratchRegister, signature_hash_op);
3582  }
3583  Label fail, ok;
3584  j(Condition::kNotEqual, &fail, Label::Distance::kNear);
3585  jmp(&ok, Label::Distance::kNear);
3586 
3587  bind(&fail);
3588  Abort(AbortReason::kWasmSignatureMismatch);
3589 
3590  bind(&ok);
3591  Operand target_op{target, 0};
3592 #else
3593  static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == 8);
3594  Operand target_op{kScratchRegister, target, ScaleFactor::times_8, 0};
3595 #endif
3596 
3597  if (call_jump_mode == CallJumpMode::kTailCall) {
3598  jmp(target_op);
3599  } else {
3600  call(target_op);
3601  }
3602 }
3603 
3604 void MacroAssembler::CallWasmCodePointerNoSignatureCheck(Register target) {
3605  Move(kScratchRegister, ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table());
3606 
3607 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
3608  static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == 16);
3609  // Check that using a 32-bit shift is valid for any valid code pointer.
3610  static_assert(wasm::WasmCodePointerTable::kMaxWasmCodePointers <=
3611  (kMaxInt >> 4));
3612  shll(target, Immediate(4));
3613  call(Operand(kScratchRegister, target, ScaleFactor::times_1, 0));
3614 #else
3615  static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == 8);
3616  call(Operand(kScratchRegister, target, ScaleFactor::times_8, 0));
3617 #endif
3618 }

3625 #endif

3627 void MacroAssembler::PextrdPreSse41(Register dst, XMMRegister src,
3628  uint8_t imm8) {

3630  Movd(dst, src);
3631  return;

3639 template <typename Op>
3640 void PinsrdPreSse41Helper(MacroAssembler* masm, XMMRegister dst, Op src,
3641  uint8_t imm8, uint32_t* load_pc_offset) {
3642  masm->Movd(kScratchDoubleReg, src);
3643  if (load_pc_offset) *load_pc_offset = masm->pc_offset();
3644  if (imm8 == 1) {
3645  masm->punpckldq(dst, kScratchDoubleReg);
3646  } else {
3647  DCHECK_EQ(0, imm8);
3648  masm->Movss(dst, kScratchDoubleReg);
3649  }
3650 }
3651 } // namespace

3675 void MacroAssembler::Lzcntl(Register dst, Register src) {
3676  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LZCNT)) {
3677  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, LZCNT);
3678  lzcntl(dst, src);
3679  return;
3680  }
3681  Label not_zero_src;
3682  bsrl(dst, src);
3683  j(not_zero, &not_zero_src, Label::kNear);
3684  Move(dst, 63); // 63^31 == 32
3685  bind(&not_zero_src);
3686  xorl(dst, Immediate(31)); // for x in [0..31], 31^x == 31 - x
3687 }

3696  bsrl(dst, src);
3697  j(not_zero, &not_zero_src, Label::kNear);
3698  Move(dst, 63); // 63^31 == 32
3699  bind(&not_zero_src);
3700  xorl(dst, Immediate(31)); // for x in [0..31], 31^x == 31 - x
3701 }

3821 void MacroAssembler::PushStackHandler() {
3822  // Adjust this code if not the case.
3823  static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kSize == 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
3824  static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0);
3825 
3826  Push(Immediate(0)); // Padding.
3827 
3828  // Link the current handler as the next handler.
3829  ExternalReference handler_address =
3830  ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate());
3831  Push(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(handler_address));
3832 
3833  // Set this new handler as the current one.
3834  movq(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(handler_address), rsp);
3835 }
3836 
3837 void MacroAssembler::PopStackHandler() {
3838  static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0);
3839  ExternalReference handler_address =
3840  ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate());
3841  Pop(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(handler_address));
3842  addq(rsp, Immediate(StackHandlerConstants::kSize - kSystemPointerSize));
3843 }
3844 
3845 void MacroAssembler::Ret() { ret(0); }
3846 
3847 void MacroAssembler::Ret(int bytes_dropped, Register scratch) {
3848  if (is_uint16(bytes_dropped)) {
3849  ret(bytes_dropped);
3850  } else {
3851  PopReturnAddressTo(scratch);
3852  addq(rsp, Immediate(bytes_dropped));
3853  PushReturnAddressFrom(scratch);
3854  ret(0);
3855  }
3856 }
3857 
3858 void MacroAssembler::IncsspqIfSupported(Register number_of_words,
3859  Register scratch) {
3860  // Optimized code can validate at runtime whether the cpu supports the
3861  // incsspq instruction, so it shouldn't use this method.
3862  CHECK(isolate()->IsGeneratingEmbeddedBuiltins());
3863  DCHECK_NE(number_of_words, scratch);
3864  Label not_supported;
3865  ExternalReference supports_cetss =
3866  ExternalReference::supports_cetss_address();
3867  Operand supports_cetss_operand =
3868  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(supports_cetss, scratch);
3869  cmpb(supports_cetss_operand, Immediate(0));
3870  j(equal, &not_supported, Label::kNear);
3871  incsspq(number_of_words);
3872  bind(&not_supported);
3873 }

3875 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
3876 void MacroAssembler::CompareInstanceTypeWithUniqueCompressedMap(
3877  Register map, InstanceType type) {
3878  std::optional<RootIndex> expected =
3879  InstanceTypeChecker::UniqueMapOfInstanceType(type);
3880  CHECK(expected);
3881  Tagged_t expected_ptr = ReadOnlyRootPtr(*expected);
3882  cmp_tagged(map, Immediate(expected_ptr));
3883 }

3889  LoadCompressedMap(compressed_map_scratch, object);

3894 void MacroAssembler::IsObjectType(Register heap_object, InstanceType type,
3895  Register map) {
3896 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
3897  if (InstanceTypeChecker::UniqueMapOfInstanceType(type)) {
3898  LoadCompressedMap(map, heap_object);
3899  CompareInstanceTypeWithUniqueCompressedMap(map, type);
3900  return;
3901  }
3902 #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
3903  CmpObjectType(heap_object, type, map);
3904 }

3906 void MacroAssembler::IsObjectTypeInRange(Register heap_object,
3907  InstanceType lower_limit,
3908  InstanceType higher_limit,
3909  Register scratch) {
3910  DCHECK_LT(lower_limit, higher_limit);
3911 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
3912  if (auto range = InstanceTypeChecker::UniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRange(
3913  lower_limit, higher_limit)) {
3914  LoadCompressedMap(scratch, heap_object);
3915  CompareRange(scratch, range->first, range->second);
3916  return;
3917  }
3918 #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
3919  LoadMap(scratch, heap_object);
3920  CmpInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, lower_limit, higher_limit);
3921 }
3922 
3923 void MacroAssembler::JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(Register heap_object,
3924  Register scratch, Label* target,
3925  Label::Distance distance,
3926  Condition cc) {
3927  CHECK(cc == Condition::kUnsignedLessThan ||
3928  cc == Condition::kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual);
3929  if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL) {
3930 #ifdef DEBUG
3931  Label ok;
3932  LoadMap(scratch, heap_object);
3933  CmpInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE,
3934  LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE);
3935  j(Condition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual, &ok, Label::Distance::kNear);
3936  LoadMap(scratch, heap_object);
3937  CmpInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, FIRST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE,
3938  LAST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE);
3939  j(Condition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual, &ok, Label::Distance::kNear);
3940  Abort(AbortReason::kInvalidReceiver);
3941  bind(&ok);
3942 #endif // DEBUG
3943 
3944  // All primitive object's maps are allocated at the start of the read only
3945  // heap. Thus JS_RECEIVER's must have maps with larger (compressed)
3946  // addresses.
3947  LoadCompressedMap(scratch, heap_object);
3948  cmp_tagged(scratch, Immediate(InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit));
3949  } else {
3950  static_assert(LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE == LAST_TYPE);
3951  CmpObjectType(heap_object, FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE, scratch);
3952  }
3953  j(cc, target, distance);
3954 }

3957  Register map) {
3958  LoadMap(map, heap_object);
3959  CmpInstanceType(map, type);
3960 }

3966 void MacroAssembler::CmpInstanceTypeRange(Register map,
3967  Register instance_type_out,
3968  InstanceType lower_limit,
3969  InstanceType higher_limit) {
3970  DCHECK_LT(lower_limit, higher_limit);
3971  movzxwl(instance_type_out, FieldOperand(map, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
3972  CompareRange(instance_type_out, lower_limit, higher_limit);

3975 void MacroAssembler::TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(Register code) {
3976  const int kByteWithDeoptBitOffset = 0 * kByteSize;
3977  const int kByteWithDeoptBitOffsetInBits = kByteWithDeoptBitOffset * 8;
3978  static_assert(V8_TARGET_LITTLE_ENDIAN == 1);
3979  static_assert(FIELD_SIZE(Code::kFlagsOffset) * kBitsPerByte == 32);
3980  static_assert(Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit >
3981  kByteWithDeoptBitOffsetInBits);
3982  testb(FieldOperand(code, Code::kFlagsOffset + kByteWithDeoptBitOffset),
3983  Immediate(1 << (Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit -
3984  kByteWithDeoptBitOffsetInBits)));
3985 }

3987 void MacroAssembler::TestCodeIsTurbofanned(Register code) {

3989  Immediate(1 << Code::kIsTurbofannedBit));
3990 }

4062 void MacroAssembler::AssertSmiOrHeapObjectInMainCompressionCage(
4063  Register object) {
4064  if (!PointerCompressionIsEnabled()) return;
4065  if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
4066  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4067  Label ok;
4068  // We may not have any scratch registers so we preserve our input register.
4069  pushq(object);
4070  j(CheckSmi(object), &ok);
4071  // Clear the lower 32 bits.
4072  shrq(object, Immediate(32));
4073  shlq(object, Immediate(32));
4074  // Either the value is now equal to the pointer compression cage base or it's
4075  // zero if we got a compressed pointer register as input.
4076  j(zero, &ok);
4077  cmpq(object, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister);
4078  Check(equal, AbortReason::kObjectNotTagged);
4079  bind(&ok);
4080  popq(object);
4081 }

4168 void MacroAssembler::AssertJSAny(Register object, Register map_tmp,
4169  AbortReason abort_reason) {
4170  if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
4171 
4172  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4173  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, map_tmp));
4174  Label ok;
4175 
4176  Label::Distance dist = DEBUG_BOOL ? Label::kFar : Label::kNear;
4177 
4178  JumpIfSmi(object, &ok, dist);
4179 
4180  LoadMap(map_tmp, object);
4181  CmpInstanceType(map_tmp, LAST_NAME_TYPE);
4182  j(below_equal, &ok, dist);
4183 
4184  CmpInstanceType(map_tmp, FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE);
4185  j(above_equal, &ok, dist);
4186 
4187  CompareRoot(map_tmp, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
4188  j(equal, &ok, dist);
4189 
4190  CompareRoot(map_tmp, RootIndex::kBigIntMap);
4191  j(equal, &ok, dist);
4192 
4193  CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4194  j(equal, &ok, dist);
4195 
4196  CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
4197  j(equal, &ok, dist);
4198 
4199  CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
4200  j(equal, &ok, dist);
4201 
4202  CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kNullValue);
4203  j(equal, &ok, dist);
4204 
4205  Abort(abort_reason);
4206 
4207  bind(&ok);
4208 }

4226 void MacroAssembler::EmitIncrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value) {
4227  DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
4228  if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
4229  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4230  Operand counter_operand =
4231  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(ExternalReference::Create(counter));
4232  // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
4233  // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t dummy_stats_counter_
4234  // field.
4235  if (value == 1) {
4236  incl(counter_operand);
4237  } else {
4238  addl(counter_operand, Immediate(value));
4239  }
4240  }
4241 }
4242 
4243 void MacroAssembler::EmitDecrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value) {
4244  DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
4245  if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
4246  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4247  Operand counter_operand =
4248  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(ExternalReference::Create(counter));
4249  // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
4250  // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t dummy_stats_counter_
4251  // field.
4252  if (value == 1) {
4253  decl(counter_operand);
4254  } else {
4255  subl(counter_operand, Immediate(value));
4256  }
4257  }
4258 }

4260 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4261 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunction(
4262  Register function, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
4263  InvokeType type, ArgumentAdaptionMode argument_adaption_mode) {
4264  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4265  DCHECK_EQ(function, rdi);
4266  LoadTaggedField(rsi, FieldOperand(function, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
4267  InvokeFunctionCode(rdi, new_target, actual_parameter_count, type,
4268  argument_adaption_mode);
4269 }
4270 
4271 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(
4272  Register function, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
4273  InvokeType type, ArgumentAdaptionMode argument_adaption_mode) {
4274  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4275  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
4276  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
4277  DCHECK_EQ(function, rdi);
4278  DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == rdx);
4279 
4280  Register dispatch_handle = kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister;
4281  movl(dispatch_handle,
4282  FieldOperand(function, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
4283 
4284  AssertFunction(function);
4285 
4286  // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
4287  Label debug_hook, continue_after_hook;
4288  {
4289  ExternalReference debug_hook_active =
4290  ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate());
4291  Operand debug_hook_active_operand =
4292  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(debug_hook_active);
4293  cmpb(debug_hook_active_operand, Immediate(0));
4294  j(not_equal, &debug_hook);
4295  }
4296  bind(&continue_after_hook);
4297 
4298  // Clear the new.target register if not given.
4299  if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
4300  LoadRoot(rdx, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4301  }
4302 
4303  if (argument_adaption_mode == ArgumentAdaptionMode::kAdapt) {
4304  Register expected_parameter_count = rbx;
4305  LoadParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(expected_parameter_count,
4306  dispatch_handle);
4307  InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, type);
4308  }
4309 
4310  // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
4311  // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
4312  // call sites.
4313  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == rcx, "ABI mismatch");
4314  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(rcx, dispatch_handle);
4315  switch (type) {
4316  case InvokeType::kCall:
4317  call(rcx);
4318  break;
4319  case InvokeType::kJump:
4320  jmp(rcx);
4321  break;
4322  }
4323  Label done;
4324  jmp(&done, Label::kNear);
4325 
4326  // Deferred debug hook.
4327  bind(&debug_hook);
4328  CallDebugOnFunctionCall(function, new_target, dispatch_handle,
4329  actual_parameter_count);
4330  jmp(&continue_after_hook);
4331 
4332  bind(&done);
4333 }
4334 #else
4335 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunction(Register function, Register new_target,
4336  Register actual_parameter_count,
4337  InvokeType type) {
4338  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4339  LoadTaggedField(
4340  rbx, FieldOperand(function, JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset));
4341  movzxwq(rbx,
4342  FieldOperand(rbx, SharedFunctionInfo::kFormalParameterCountOffset));
4343 
4344  InvokeFunction(function, new_target, rbx, actual_parameter_count, type);
4345 }
4346 
4347 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunction(Register function, Register new_target,
4348  Register expected_parameter_count,
4349  Register actual_parameter_count,
4350  InvokeType type) {
4351  DCHECK_EQ(function, rdi);
4352  LoadTaggedField(rsi, FieldOperand(function, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
4353  InvokeFunctionCode(rdi, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
4354  actual_parameter_count, type);
4355 }
4356 
4357 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(Register function, Register new_target,
4358  Register expected_parameter_count,
4359  Register actual_parameter_count,
4360  InvokeType type) {
4361  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4362  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
4363  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
4364  DCHECK_EQ(function, rdi);
4365  DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == rdx);
4366 
4367  AssertFunction(function);
4368 
4369  // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
4370  Label debug_hook, continue_after_hook;
4371  {
4372  ExternalReference debug_hook_active =
4373  ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate());
4374  Operand debug_hook_active_operand =
4375  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(debug_hook_active);
4376  cmpb(debug_hook_active_operand, Immediate(0));
4377  j(not_equal, &debug_hook);
4378  }
4379  bind(&continue_after_hook);
4380 
4381  // Clear the new.target register if not given.
4382  if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
4383  LoadRoot(rdx, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4384  }
4385 
4386  Label done;
4387  InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, type);
4388  // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
4389  // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
4390  // call sites.
4391  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == rcx, "ABI mismatch");
4392  constexpr int unused_argument_count = 0;
4393  switch (type) {
4394  case InvokeType::kCall:
4395  CallJSFunction(function, unused_argument_count);
4396  break;
4397  case InvokeType::kJump:
4398  JumpJSFunction(function);
4399  break;
4400  }
4401  jmp(&done, Label::kNear);
4402 
4403  // Deferred debug hook.
4404  bind(&debug_hook);
4405  CallDebugOnFunctionCall(function, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
4406  actual_parameter_count);
4407  jmp(&continue_after_hook);
4408 
4409  bind(&done);
4410 }
4411 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4412 
4413 Operand MacroAssembler::StackLimitAsOperand(StackLimitKind kind) {
4414  DCHECK(root_array_available());
4415  intptr_t offset = kind == StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit
4416  ? IsolateData::real_jslimit_offset()
4417  : IsolateData::jslimit_offset();
4418 
4419  CHECK(is_int32(offset));
4420  return Operand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
4421 }
4422 
4423 void MacroAssembler::StackOverflowCheck(
4424  Register num_args, Label* stack_overflow,
4425  Label::Distance stack_overflow_distance) {
4426  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4427  DCHECK_NE(num_args, kScratchRegister);
4428  // Check the stack for overflow. We are not trying to catch
4429  // interruptions (e.g. debug break and preemption) here, so the "real stack
4430  // limit" is checked.
4431  movq(kScratchRegister, rsp);
4432  // Make kScratchRegister the space we have left. The stack might already be
4433  // overflowed here which will cause kScratchRegister to become negative.
4434  subq(kScratchRegister, StackLimitAsOperand(StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit));
4435  // TODO(victorgomes): Use ia32 approach with leaq, since it requires less
4436  // instructions.
4437  sarq(kScratchRegister, Immediate(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
4438  // Check if the arguments will overflow the stack.
4439  cmpq(kScratchRegister, num_args);
4440  // Signed comparison.
4441  // TODO(victorgomes): Save some bytes in the builtins that use stack checks
4442  // by jumping to a builtin that throws the exception.
4443  j(less_equal, stack_overflow, stack_overflow_distance);
4444 }
4445 
4446 void MacroAssembler::InvokePrologue(Register expected_parameter_count,
4447  Register actual_parameter_count,
4448  InvokeType type) {
4449  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4450  if (expected_parameter_count == actual_parameter_count) {
4451  Move(rax, actual_parameter_count);
4452  return;
4453  }
4454  Label regular_invoke;
4455 
4456  // If overapplication or if the actual argument count is equal to the
4457  // formal parameter count, no need to push extra undefined values.
4458  subq(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count);
4459  j(less_equal, &regular_invoke, Label::kFar);
4460 
4461  Label stack_overflow;
4462  StackOverflowCheck(expected_parameter_count, &stack_overflow);
4463 
4464  // Underapplication. Move the arguments already in the stack, including the
4465  // receiver and the return address.
4466  {
4467  Label copy, check;
4468  Register src = r8, dest = rsp, num = r9, current = r11;
4469  movq(src, rsp);
4470  leaq(kScratchRegister,
4471  Operand(expected_parameter_count, times_system_pointer_size, 0));
4472  AllocateStackSpace(kScratchRegister);
4473  // Extra words are for the return address (if a jump).
4474  int extra_words =
4475  type == InvokeType::kCall ? 0 : kReturnAddressStackSlotCount;
4476 
4477  leaq(num, Operand(rax, extra_words)); // Number of words to copy.
4478  Move(current, 0);
4479  // Fall-through to the loop body because there are non-zero words to copy.
4480  bind(&copy);
4481  movq(kScratchRegister,
4482  Operand(src, current, times_system_pointer_size, 0));
4483  movq(Operand(dest, current, times_system_pointer_size, 0),
4484  kScratchRegister);
4485  incq(current);
4486  bind(&check);
4487  cmpq(current, num);
4488  j(less, &copy);
4489  leaq(r8, Operand(rsp, num, times_system_pointer_size, 0));
4490  }
4491  // Fill remaining expected arguments with undefined values.
4492  LoadRoot(kScratchRegister, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4493  {
4494  Label loop;
4495  bind(&loop);
4496  decq(expected_parameter_count);
4497  movq(Operand(r8, expected_parameter_count, times_system_pointer_size, 0),
4498  kScratchRegister);
4499  j(greater, &loop, Label::kNear);
4500  }
4501  jmp(&regular_invoke);
4502 
4503  bind(&stack_overflow);
4504  {
4505  FrameScope frame(
4506  this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
4507  CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
4508  int3(); // This should be unreachable.
4509  }
4510  bind(&regular_invoke);
4511 }
4512 
4513 void MacroAssembler::CallDebugOnFunctionCall(
4514  Register fun, Register new_target,
4515  Register expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle,
4516  Register actual_parameter_count) {
4517  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4518  // Load receiver to pass it later to DebugOnFunctionCall hook.
4519  // Receiver is located on top of the stack if we have a frame (usually a
4520  // construct frame), or after the return address if we do not yet have a
4521  // frame.
4522  movq(kScratchRegister, Operand(rsp, has_frame() ? 0 : kSystemPointerSize));
4523 
4524  FrameScope frame(
4525  this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
4526 
4527  SmiTag(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
4528  Push(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
4529 
4530  SmiTag(actual_parameter_count);
4531  Push(actual_parameter_count);
4532  SmiUntag(actual_parameter_count);
4533 
4534  if (new_target.is_valid()) {
4535  Push(new_target);
4536  }
4537  Push(fun);
4538  Push(fun);
4539  Push(kScratchRegister);
4540  CallRuntime(Runtime::kDebugOnFunctionCall);
4541  Pop(fun);
4542  if (new_target.is_valid()) {
4543  Pop(new_target);
4544  }
4545  Pop(actual_parameter_count);
4546  SmiUntag(actual_parameter_count);
4547  Pop(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
4548  SmiUntag(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
4549 }
4550 
4551 void MacroAssembler::StubPrologue(StackFrame::Type type) {
4552  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4553  pushq(rbp); // Caller's frame pointer.
4554  movq(rbp, rsp);
4555  Push(Immediate(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(type)));
4556 }
4557 
4558 void MacroAssembler::Prologue() {
4559  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4560  pushq(rbp); // Caller's frame pointer.
4561  movq(rbp, rsp);
4562  Push(kContextRegister); // Callee's context.
4563  Push(kJSFunctionRegister); // Callee's JS function.
4564  Push(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister); // Actual argument count.
4565 }

4567 void MacroAssembler::EnterFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
4568  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4569  pushq(rbp);
4570  movq(rbp, rsp);
4571  if (!StackFrame::IsJavaScript(type)) {
4572  static_assert(CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset ==
4573  -kSystemPointerSize);
4574  Push(Immediate(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(type)));
4575  }
4576 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4577  if (type == StackFrame::WASM) Push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
4578 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4579 }
4580 
4581 void MacroAssembler::LeaveFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
4582  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4583  // TODO(v8:11429): Consider passing BASELINE instead, and checking for
4584  // IsJSFrame or similar. Could then unify with manual frame leaves in the
4585  // interpreter too.
4586  if (v8_flags.debug_code && !StackFrame::IsJavaScript(type)) {
4587  cmpq(Operand(rbp, CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset),
4588  Immediate(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(type)));
4589  Check(equal, AbortReason::kStackFrameTypesMustMatch);
4590  }
4591  movq(rsp, rbp);
4592  popq(rbp);
4593 }
4594 
4595 #if defined(V8_TARGET_OS_WIN) || defined(V8_TARGET_OS_MACOS)
4596 void MacroAssembler::AllocateStackSpace(Register bytes_scratch) {
4597  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4598  // On Windows and on macOS, we cannot increment the stack size by more than
4599  // one page (minimum page size is 4KB) without accessing at least one byte on
4600  // the page. Check this:
4601  // https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa227153(v=vs.60).aspx.
4602  Label check_offset;
4603  Label touch_next_page;
4604  jmp(&check_offset);
4605  bind(&touch_next_page);
4606  subq(rsp, Immediate(kStackPageSize));
4607  // Just to touch the page, before we increment further.
4608  movb(Operand(rsp, 0), Immediate(0));
4609  subq(bytes_scratch, Immediate(kStackPageSize));
4610 
4611  bind(&check_offset);
4612  cmpq(bytes_scratch, Immediate(kStackPageSize));
4613  j(greater_equal, &touch_next_page);
4614 
4615  subq(rsp, bytes_scratch);
4616 }
4617 
4618 void MacroAssembler::AllocateStackSpace(int bytes) {
4619  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4620  DCHECK_GE(bytes, 0);
4621  while (bytes >= kStackPageSize) {
4622  subq(rsp, Immediate(kStackPageSize));
4623  movb(Operand(rsp, 0), Immediate(0));
4624  bytes -= kStackPageSize;
4625  }
4626  if (bytes == 0) return;
4627  subq(rsp, Immediate(bytes));
4628 }
4629 #endif
4630 
4631 void MacroAssembler::EnterExitFrame(int extra_slots,
4632  StackFrame::Type frame_type,
4633  Register c_function) {
4634  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4635  DCHECK(frame_type == StackFrame::EXIT ||
4636  frame_type == StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT ||
4637  frame_type == StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT ||
4638  frame_type == StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT);
4639 
4640  // Set up the frame structure on the stack.
4641  // All constants are relative to the frame pointer of the exit frame.
4642  DCHECK_EQ(kFPOnStackSize + kPCOnStackSize,
4643  ExitFrameConstants::kCallerSPDisplacement);
4644  DCHECK_EQ(kFPOnStackSize, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset);
4645  DCHECK_EQ(0 * kSystemPointerSize, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset);
4646  pushq(rbp);
4647  movq(rbp, rsp);
4648 
4649  Push(Immediate(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(frame_type)));
4650  DCHECK_EQ(-2 * kSystemPointerSize, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset);
4651  Push(Immediate(0)); // Saved entry sp, patched below.
4652 
4653  DCHECK(!AreAliased(rbp, kContextRegister, c_function));
4654  using ER = ExternalReference;
4655  Store(ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate()), rbp);
4656  Store(ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate()),
4657  kContextRegister);
4658  Store(ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCFunctionAddress, isolate()), c_function);
4659 
4660 #ifdef V8_TARGET_OS_WIN
4661  // Note this is only correct under the assumption that the caller hasn't
4662  // considered home stack slots already.
4663  // TODO(jgruber): This is a bit hacky since the caller in most cases still
4664  // needs to know about the home stack slots in order to address reserved
4665  // slots. Consider moving this fully into caller code.
4666  extra_slots += kWindowsHomeStackSlots;
4667 #endif
4668  AllocateStackSpace(extra_slots * kSystemPointerSize);
4669 
4670  AlignStackPointer();
4671 
4672  // Patch the saved entry sp.
4673  movq(Operand(rbp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset), rsp);
4674 }
4675 
4676 void MacroAssembler::LeaveExitFrame() {
4677  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4678 
4679  leave();
4680 
4681  // Restore the current context from top and clear it in debug mode.
4682  ExternalReference context_address =
4683  ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
4684  Operand context_operand = ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address);
4685  movq(rsi, context_operand);
4686 #ifdef DEBUG
4687  Move(context_operand, Context::kNoContext);
4688 #endif
4689 
4690  // Clear the top frame.
4691  ExternalReference c_entry_fp_address =
4692  ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
4693  Operand c_entry_fp_operand = ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address);
4694  Move(c_entry_fp_operand, 0);
4695 }
4696 
4697 void MacroAssembler::LoadNativeContextSlot(Register dst, int index) {
4698  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4699  // Load native context.
4700  LoadMap(dst, rsi);
4701  LoadTaggedField(
4702  dst,
4703  FieldOperand(dst, Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset));
4704  // Load value from native context.
4705  LoadTaggedField(dst, Operand(dst, Context::SlotOffset(index)));
4706 }
4707 
4708 void MacroAssembler::TryLoadOptimizedOsrCode(Register scratch_and_result,
4709  CodeKind min_opt_level,
4710  Register feedback_vector,
4711  FeedbackSlot slot,
4712  Label* on_result,
4713  Label::Distance distance) {
4714  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4715  Label fallthrough, on_mark_deopt;
4716  LoadTaggedField(
4717  scratch_and_result,
4718  FieldOperand(feedback_vector,
4719  FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt())));
4720  LoadWeakValue(scratch_and_result, &fallthrough);
4721 
4722  // Is it marked_for_deoptimization? If yes, clear the slot.
4723  {
4724  // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
4725  LoadCodePointerField(
4726  scratch_and_result,
4727  FieldOperand(scratch_and_result, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset),
4728  kScratchRegister);
4729 
4730  TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(scratch_and_result);
4731 
4732  if (min_opt_level == CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS) {
4733  j(not_zero, &on_mark_deopt, Label::Distance::kNear);
4734 
4735  TestCodeIsTurbofanned(scratch_and_result);
4736  j(not_zero, on_result, distance);
4737  jmp(&fallthrough);
4738  } else {
4739  DCHECK_EQ(min_opt_level, CodeKind::MAGLEV);
4740  j(equal, on_result, distance);
4741  }
4742 
4743  bind(&on_mark_deopt);
4744  StoreTaggedField(
4745  FieldOperand(feedback_vector,
4746  FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt())),
4747  ClearedValue());
4748  }
4749 
4750  bind(&fallthrough);
4751  Move(scratch_and_result, 0);
4752 }

4754 int MacroAssembler::ArgumentStackSlotsForCFunctionCall(int num_arguments) {
4755  DCHECK_GE(num_arguments, 0);
4756 #ifdef V8_TARGET_OS_WIN
4757  return std::max(num_arguments, kWindowsHomeStackSlots);
4758 #else
4759  return std::max(num_arguments - kRegisterPassedArguments, 0);
4760 #endif
4761 }
4762 
4763 void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_arguments) {
4764  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4765  int frame_alignment = base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
4766  DCHECK_NE(frame_alignment, 0);
4767  DCHECK_GE(num_arguments, 0);
4768 
4769  // Make stack end at alignment and allocate space for arguments and old rsp.
4770  movq(kScratchRegister, rsp);
4771  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
4772  int argument_slots_on_stack =
4773  ArgumentStackSlotsForCFunctionCall(num_arguments);
4774  AllocateStackSpace((argument_slots_on_stack + 1) * kSystemPointerSize);
4775  andq(rsp, Immediate(-frame_alignment));
4776  movq(Operand(rsp, argument_slots_on_stack * kSystemPointerSize),
4777  kScratchRegister);
4778 }

4780 int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(ExternalReference function, int num_arguments,
4781  SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
4782  Label* return_location) {
4783  // Note: The "CallCFunction" code comment will be generated by the other
4784  // CallCFunction method called below.
4785  LoadAddress(rax, function);
4786  return CallCFunction(rax, num_arguments, set_isolate_data_slots,
4787  return_location, CodeSandboxingMode::kUnsandboxed);
4788 }
4789 
4790 int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(Register function, int num_arguments,
4791  SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
4792  Label* return_location,
4793  CodeSandboxingMode target_sandboxing_mode) {
4794  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4795  DCHECK_LE(num_arguments, kMaxCParameters);
4796  DCHECK(has_frame());
4797  // Check stack alignment.
4798  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4799  CheckStackAlignment();
4800  }
4801 
4802  SwitchSandboxingModeBeforeCallIfNeeded(target_sandboxing_mode);
4803 
4804  // Save the frame pointer and PC so that the stack layout remains iterable,
4805  // even without an ExitFrame which normally exists between JS and C frames.
4806  Label get_pc;
4807 
4808  if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
4809  DCHECK(!AreAliased(kScratchRegister, function));
4810  leaq(kScratchRegister, Operand(&get_pc, 0));
4811 
4812  CHECK(root_array_available());
4813  movq(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerPC),
4814  kScratchRegister);
4815  movq(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP), rbp);
4816  }
4817 
4818  call(function);
4819  int call_pc_offset = pc_offset();
4820  bind(&get_pc);
4821  if (return_location) bind(return_location);
4822 
4823  DCHECK_NE(base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment(), 0);
4824  DCHECK_GE(num_arguments, 0);
4825  int argument_slots_on_stack =
4826  ArgumentStackSlotsForCFunctionCall(num_arguments);
4827  // Restoring the stack pointer has to happen right after the call. The
4828  // deoptimizer may overwrite everything after restoring the SP.
4829  int before_offset = pc_offset();
4830  movq(rsp, Operand(rsp, argument_slots_on_stack * kSystemPointerSize));
4831  Nop(kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall - (pc_offset() - before_offset));
4832  // We assume that with the nop padding, the move instruction uses
4833  // kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall bytes. When we patch in the deopt trampoline,
4834  // we patch it in after the move instruction, so that the stack has been
4835  // restored correctly.
4836  CHECK_EQ(kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall, pc_offset() - before_offset);
4837 
4838  if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
4839  // We don't unset the PC; the FP is the source of truth.
4840  movq(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP),
4841  Immediate(0));
4842  }
4843 
4844  SwitchSandboxingModeAfterCallIfNeeded(target_sandboxing_mode);
4845 
4846  return call_pc_offset;
4847 }
4848 
4849 void MacroAssembler::MemoryChunkHeaderFromObject(Register object,
4850  Register header) {
4851  constexpr intptr_t alignment_mask =
4852  MemoryChunk::GetAlignmentMaskForAssembler();
4853  if (header == object) {
4854  andq(header, Immediate(~alignment_mask));
4855  } else {
4856  movq(header, Immediate(~alignment_mask));
4857  andq(header, object);
4858  }
4859 }
4860 
4861 void MacroAssembler::CheckPageFlag(Register object, Register scratch, int mask,
4862  Condition cc, Label* condition_met,
4863  Label::Distance condition_met_distance) {
4864  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4865  DCHECK(cc == zero || cc == not_zero);
4866  MemoryChunkHeaderFromObject(object, scratch);
4867  if (mask < (1 << kBitsPerByte)) {
4868  testb(Operand(scratch, MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset()),
4869  Immediate(static_cast<uint8_t>(mask)));
4870  } else {
4871  testl(Operand(scratch, MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset()), Immediate(mask));
4872  }
4873  j(cc, condition_met, condition_met_distance);
4874 }
4875 
4876 void MacroAssembler::JumpIfMarking(Label* is_marking,
4877  Label::Distance condition_met_distance) {
4878  testb(Operand(kRootRegister, IsolateData::is_marking_flag_offset()),
4879  Immediate(static_cast<uint8_t>(1)));
4880  j(not_zero, is_marking, condition_met_distance);
4881 }
4882 
4883 void MacroAssembler::JumpIfNotMarking(Label* not_marking,
4884  Label::Distance condition_met_distance) {
4885  testb(Operand(kRootRegister, IsolateData::is_marking_flag_offset()),
4886  Immediate(static_cast<uint8_t>(1)));
4887  j(zero, not_marking, condition_met_distance);
4888 }
4889 
4890 void MacroAssembler::CheckMarkBit(Register object, Register scratch0,
4891  Register scratch1, Condition cc,
4892  Label* condition_met,
4893  Label::Distance condition_met_distance) {
4894  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4895  DCHECK(cc == carry || cc == not_carry);
4896  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, scratch0, scratch1));
4897 
4898  // Computing cell.
4899  MemoryChunkHeaderFromObject(object, scratch0);
4900 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
4901  movl(scratch0, Operand(scratch0, MemoryChunk::MetadataIndexOffset()));
4902  andl(scratch0,
4903  Immediate(MemoryChunkConstants::kMetadataPointerTableSizeMask));
4904  shll(scratch0, Immediate(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
4905  LoadAddress(scratch1,
4906  ExternalReference::memory_chunk_metadata_table_address());
4907  movq(scratch0, Operand(scratch1, scratch0, times_1, 0));
4908 #else // !V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
4909  movq(scratch0, Operand(scratch0, MemoryChunk::MetadataOffset()));
4910 #endif // !V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
4911  if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
4912  Push(object);
4913  movq(scratch1, Operand(scratch0, MemoryChunkMetadata::AreaStartOffset()));
4914  MemoryChunkHeaderFromObject(scratch1, scratch1);
4915  MemoryChunkHeaderFromObject(object, object);
4916  cmpq(object, scratch1);
4917  Check(equal, AbortReason::kMetadataAreaStartDoesNotMatch);
4918  Pop(object);
4919  }
4920  addq(scratch0, Immediate(MutablePageMetadata::MarkingBitmapOffset()));
4921 
4922  movq(scratch1, object);
4923  andq(scratch1, Immediate(MemoryChunk::GetAlignmentMaskForAssembler()));
4924  // It's important not to fold the next two shifts.
4925  shrq(scratch1, Immediate(kTaggedSizeLog2 + MarkingBitmap::kBitsPerCellLog2));
4926  shlq(scratch1, Immediate(kBitsPerByteLog2));
4927  addq(scratch0, scratch1);
4928 
4929  // Computing mask.
4930  movq(scratch1, object);
4931  andq(scratch1, Immediate(MemoryChunk::GetAlignmentMaskForAssembler()));
4932  shrq(scratch1, Immediate(kTaggedSizeLog2));
4933  andq(scratch1, Immediate(MarkingBitmap::kBitIndexMask));
4934  btq(Operand(scratch0, 0), scratch1);
4935 
4936  j(cc, condition_met, condition_met_distance);
4937 }
4938 
4939 void MacroAssembler::ComputeCodeStartAddress(Register dst) {
4940  Label current;
4941  bind(&current);
4942  int pc = pc_offset();
4943  // Load effective address to get the address of the current instruction.
4944  leaq(dst, Operand(&current, -pc));
4945 }
4946 
4947 // Check if the code object is marked for deoptimization. If it is, then it
4948 // jumps to the CompileLazyDeoptimizedCode builtin. In order to do this we need
4949 // to:
4950 // 1. read from memory the word that contains that bit, which can be found in
4951 // the flags in the referenced {Code} object;
4952 // 2. test kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit in those flags; and
4953 // 3. if it is not zero then it jumps to the builtin.
4954 //
4955 // Note: With leaptiering we simply assert the code is not deoptimized.
4956 void MacroAssembler::BailoutIfDeoptimized(Register scratch) {
4957  int offset = InstructionStream::kCodeOffset - InstructionStream::kHeaderSize;
4958  if (v8_flags.debug_code || !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL) {
4959  LoadProtectedPointerField(
4960  scratch, Operand(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister, offset));
4961  TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(scratch);
4962  }
4963 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4964  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4965  Assert(zero, AbortReason::kInvalidDeoptimizedCode);
4966  }
4967 #else
4968  TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCompileLazyDeoptimizedCode, not_zero);
4969 #endif
4970 }
4971 
4972 void MacroAssembler::CallForDeoptimization(Builtin target, int, Label* exit,
4973  DeoptimizeKind kind, Label* ret,
4974  Label*) {
4975  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4976  // Note: Assembler::call is used here on purpose to guarantee fixed-size
4977  // exits even on Atom CPUs; see MacroAssembler::Call for Atom-specific
4978  // performance tuning which emits a different instruction sequence.
4979  call(EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(target));
4980  DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(exit),
4981  (kind == DeoptimizeKind::kLazy ||
4982  kind == DeoptimizeKind::kLazyAfterFastCall)
4983  ? Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize
4984  : Deoptimizer::kEagerDeoptExitSize);
4985 }
4986 
4987 void MacroAssembler::Trap() { int3(); }
4988 void MacroAssembler::DebugBreak() { int3(); }
4989 
4990 // Calls an API function. Allocates HandleScope, extracts returned value
4991 // from handle and propagates exceptions. Clobbers C argument registers
4992 // and C caller-saved registers. Restores context. On return removes
4993 // (*argc_operand + slots_to_drop_on_return) * kSystemPointerSize
4994 // (GCed, includes the call JS arguments space and the additional space
4995 // allocated for the fast call).
4996 void CallApiFunctionAndReturn(MacroAssembler* masm, bool with_profiling,
4997  Register function_address,
4998  ExternalReference thunk_ref, Register thunk_arg,
4999  int slots_to_drop_on_return,
5000  MemOperand* argc_operand,
5001  MemOperand return_value_operand) {
5002  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
5003  Label propagate_exception;
5004  Label delete_allocated_handles;
5005  Label leave_exit_frame;
5006 
5007  using ER = ExternalReference;
5008 
5009  Isolate* isolate = masm->isolate();
5010  MemOperand next_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5011  ER::handle_scope_next_address(isolate), no_reg);
5012  MemOperand limit_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5013  ER::handle_scope_limit_address(isolate), no_reg);
5014  MemOperand level_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5015  ER::handle_scope_level_address(isolate), no_reg);
5016 
5017  Register return_value = rax;
5018  Register scratch = kCArgRegs[3];
5019 
5020  // Allocate HandleScope in callee-saved registers.
5021  // We will need to restore the HandleScope after the call to the API function,
5022  // by allocating it in callee-saved registers it'll be preserved by C code.
5023  Register prev_next_address_reg = r12;
5024  Register prev_limit_reg = r15;
5025 
5026  // C arguments (kCArgRegs[0/1]) are expected to be initialized outside, so
5027  // this function must not corrupt them. kScratchRegister might be used
5028  // implicitly by the macro assembler.
5029  DCHECK(!AreAliased(kCArgRegs[0], kCArgRegs[1], // C args
5030  return_value, scratch, kScratchRegister,
5031  prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
5032  // function_address and thunk_arg might overlap but this function must not
5033  // corrupted them until the call is made (i.e. overlap with return_value is
5034  // fine).
5035  DCHECK(!AreAliased(function_address, // incoming parameters
5036  scratch, kScratchRegister, prev_next_address_reg,
5037  prev_limit_reg));
5038  DCHECK(!AreAliased(thunk_arg, // incoming parameters
5039  scratch, kScratchRegister, prev_next_address_reg,
5040  prev_limit_reg));
5041  {
5042  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
5043  "Allocate HandleScope in callee-save registers.");
5044  __ movq(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
5045  __ movq(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
5046  __ addl(level_mem_op, Immediate(1));
5047  }
5048 
5049  DCHECK_EQ(__ sandboxing_mode(), CodeSandboxingMode::kSandboxed);
5050  __ ExitSandbox();
5051 
5052  Label profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, done_api_call;
5053  if (with_profiling) {
5054  __ RecordComment("Check if profiler or side effects check is enabled");
5055  __ cmpb(__ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kExecutionMode),
5056  Immediate(0));
5057  __ j(not_zero, &profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
5058 #ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
5059  __ RecordComment("Check if RCS is enabled");
5060  __ Move(scratch, ER::address_of_runtime_stats_flag());
5061  __ cmpl(Operand(scratch, 0), Immediate(0));
5062  __ j(not_zero, &profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
5063 #endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
5064  }
5065 
5066  __ RecordComment("Call the api function directly.");
5067  __ call(function_address);
5068  __ bind(&done_api_call);
5069 
5070  __ RecordComment("Load the value from ReturnValue");
5071  __ movq(return_value, return_value_operand);
5072 
5073  {
5074  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
5075  masm,
5076  "No more valid handles (the result handle was the last one)."
5077  "Restore previous handle scope.");
5078  __ subl(level_mem_op, Immediate(1));
5079  __ Assert(above_equal, AbortReason::kInvalidHandleScopeLevel);
5080  __ movq(next_mem_op, prev_next_address_reg);
5081  __ cmpq(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
5082  __ j(not_equal, &delete_allocated_handles);
5083  }
5084 
5085  __ RecordComment("Leave the API exit frame.");
5086  __ bind(&leave_exit_frame);
5087 
5088  Register argc_reg = prev_limit_reg;
5089  if (argc_operand != nullptr) {
5090  __ movq(argc_reg, *argc_operand);
5091  }
5092  __ LeaveExitFrame();
5093 
5094  __ EnterSandbox();
5095 
5096  {
5097  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
5098  "Check if the function scheduled an exception.");
5099  __ CompareRoot(
5100  __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(ER::exception_address(isolate), no_reg),
5101  RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
5102  __ j(not_equal, &propagate_exception);
5103  }
5104 
5105  __ AssertJSAny(return_value, scratch,
5106  AbortReason::kAPICallReturnedInvalidObject);
5107 
5108  if (argc_operand == nullptr) {
5109  DCHECK_NE(slots_to_drop_on_return, 0);
5110  __ ret(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize);
5111  } else {
5112  __ PopReturnAddressTo(scratch);
5113  // {argc_operand} was loaded into {argc_reg} above.
5114  __ leaq(rsp, Operand(rsp, argc_reg, times_system_pointer_size,
5115  slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
5116  // Push and ret (instead of jmp) to keep the RSB and the CET shadow stack
5117  // balanced.
5118  __ PushReturnAddressFrom(scratch);
5119  __ ret(0);
5120  }
5121  if (with_profiling) {
5122  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Call the api function via thunk wrapper.");
5123  // Call the api function via thunk wrapper.
5124  __ bind(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
5125  // Additional parameter is the address of the actual callback function.
5126  if (thunk_arg.is_valid()) {
5127  MemOperand thunk_arg_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5128  IsolateFieldId::kApiCallbackThunkArgument);
5129  __ movq(thunk_arg_mem_op, thunk_arg);
5130  }
5131  __ Call(thunk_ref);
5132  __ jmp(&done_api_call);
5133  }
5134  __ RecordComment("An exception was thrown. Propagate it.");
5135  __ bind(&propagate_exception);
5136  __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kPropagateException);
5137  {
5138  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
5139  masm, "HandleScope limit has changed. Delete allocated extensions.");
5140  __ bind(&delete_allocated_handles);
5141  __ movq(limit_mem_op, prev_limit_reg);
5142  // Save the return value in a callee-save register.
5143  Register saved_result = prev_limit_reg;
5144  __ movq(saved_result, return_value);
5145  __ LoadAddress(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address());
5146  __ Call(ER::delete_handle_scope_extensions());
5147  __ movq(return_value, saved_result);
5148  __ jmp(&leave_exit_frame);
5149  }
5150 }
5151 
5152 } // namespace internal
5153 } // namespace v8
5154 
5155 #undef __
5156 
5157 #endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64
